title: *skillet squash au gratin
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add squash, onion, salt, pepper and water or tomatoes.
Cook, covered, for 10 minutes or longer, until squash is tender.
Sprinkle with cheese and a teaspoon of soy sauce, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: robin's dip
directions: Cook hamburger and sausage until brown and crumbly, drain. In a large pot combine meat and remaining ingredients. Heat until cheese is melted, stirring constantly. Serve warm.

title: savory chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in 2-quart baking dish.
Mix soup and milk. Pour over chicken; add onion and celery.
Add stuffing mix.
Pour melted margarine and broth over stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: boiled fudge cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat, then add oats, peanut butter, vanilla and pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Cool for approximately 1 hour.

title: chocolate oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, soda and salt, mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies, 12 to 13 minutes for crispy cookies. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet, remove to wire rack.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Make "sandwiches" with peanut butter between crackers.
Melt almond bark (2 blocks at a time) in microwave.
Using tongs, dip sandwiches in almond bark until completely coated.
Place on covered cookie sheet.
Chill.

title: lemon-herb green beans
directions: Rinse and trim green beans. Add beans to boiling salted water. Cook, uncovered, on medium-high heat, 7 minutes. Drain. Return beans to saucepan. Stir in remaining ingredients. Let stand 5 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook sausage and onion in a large Dutch oven over medium high heat until sausage is browned and onion is tender.
Add green pepper, if desired.
Add kidney beans, catsup and garlic, stirring well.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours. Serve over rice.

title: polynesian chicken salad
directions: Combine in a large bowl the rice, chicken or turkey, pineapple, grapes and water chestnuts.
Add cashews.

title: chocolate drops
directions: Add sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Bring to a boil; boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add quick cooking oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until mixed well.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.
Children love these.

title: diet pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into crust.
Chill.

title: walnut squares
directions: Beat egg until foamy.
Beat in brown sugar.
Sift together and stir in dry ingredients.
Mix in walnuts.
Spread in greased square pan and bake at 325° until top has a dull crust, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.
Cool; remove from pan.

title: savory pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Trim fat from meat and cook, using 1 tablespoon liquid fat.
Combine salt, marjoram, thyme and sage. Sprinkle on meat and press with fingers.
Brown meat on both sides (using cooked fat).
Transfer to shallow dish.
Combine chicken broth, orange rind and ginger.
Pour over chops.
Cover and bake 45 minutes.
One chop contains 285 calories.

title: company carrots
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Add carrots and green onions.
Cover tightly and cook slowly over low heat for 1 hour. Do not add water. Serves 6.

title: boston brown bread
directions: In a small bowl, sift together flour, corn meal, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Stir in wheat flour.
Combine egg, butter, molasses and buttermilk.
Add to dry ingredients along with cheese and stir only to blend.
Toss raisins with the 1 tablespoon flour; stir into batter.
Pour batter into a 9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch buttered loaf pan.
Cover top of pan with double thickness of aluminum foil.
Place in shallow baking pan. Surround loaf pan with water.
Bake in a preheated oven of 350° for 2 hours.
Remove from oven and cool for 10 minutes.
Serve warm with butter.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix together with a fork.
Roll out between wax paper.
Bake at 450° until lightly brown.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
and
beat well.	Pour into angel food cake
pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done. Serve plain, with icing or whipped cream.

title: snow salad
directions: Beat egg yolks, sugar and salt and add to milk.
Boil this mixture slowly until thickens; set aside to cool.
(May curdle a little but doesn't hurt.)
Add to pears, pineapple and marshmallows.
Add stiffly beaten whipping cream or Cool Whip to other mixture.
Let set half day before serving.

title: cherry pie mix salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk first, then add rest of ingredients and set in fridge until needed.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Peel and devein fresh shrimp.
Fry bacon.
Save bacon.
Saute onions and peppers in bacon drippings.
Add shrimp, saute until shrimp turns pink. Thicken with cornstarch.
Add salt, pepper, garlic salt and hot sauce to taste.
Add stewed tomatoes and water.
Bring to boil.
Add rice.
Cook until tender.
Add crumbled bacon.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate until chilled, about 1 hour.

title: potato wedges
directions: Pour oil in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Place prepared potatoes in pan and turn to coat with oil.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, paprika, and parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375 for 1 hour 15 minutes. Serves 6.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Lightly butter casserole dish; add cubed bread.
Sprinkle browned and drained sausage over bread.
Mix all other ingredients, except cheese, until smooth.
Pour over bread/meat mixture.
Refrigerate overnight (or freezes nicely).
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: In a large skillet, melt 2 tablespoons of butter or margarine and saute rice until lightly browned, stirring often.
Add wine, salt, water, bouillon cubes and raisins to rice.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is tender and dry.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate (9 x 1 1/4-inch or 10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Beat all ingredients until smooth, 1 minute in blender on high speed or 2 minutes with hand mixer.
Pour into pie plate. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook berries in water.
While hot mix Jell-O and marshmallows in hot mixture.
Add sugar, celery, apple and nuts.
Pour into mold or bowl and chill.
Nice salad with chicken, turkey or ham.

title: chicken tostados(makes 12 servings)
directions: Heat shells.
In a medium skillet, quickly cook chicken and onion in butter until chicken is browned.
Add salsa and seasoning mix, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
To assemble, spread 1 heaping tablespoonful refried beans on each shell.
Spoon on approximately 1/3 cup chicken mixture.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.

title: quick potato soup
directions: Add 1 quart water to ingredients; cook until tender.
Mash well.
Add milk, salt, pepper and butter to taste.
Simmer.

title: mom's e-z chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Drain. Add rest of ingredients. Simmer and serve.

title: old fashioned sweet potato pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Warm butter in saucepan and put all ingredients in mashed potatoes.
Beat egg whites until light. Fold in egg whites and put all in pie shell.
Cook until brown at 350°.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and drain.
While hot, add margarine so it can totally melt.
Add all other ingredients and blend well.
Best, if served after chilling overnight.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix the ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top baked dish for 5 to 10 minutes to melt.
Makes a very large dish.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture with buttermilk.
Beat until blended. Stir in nuts, cherries and vanilla.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: dilled new potatoes and peas
directions: Cook potatoes in 2-quart saucepan in lightly salted boiling water, 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Add peas; cook for 1 minute.
Drain well.
Combine gravy, sour cream and dill.
Stir into vegetable mixture.
Heat (do not boil), stirring occasionally.

title: bean and franks casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until bubbly.
Serve with tossed salad and crusty bread.

title: merle's orange lemon cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour and baking powder; add to the creamed sugar and butter, alternately with milk.
Beat until creamy.
Bake in 8 or 9-inch cake pans in 4 layers.

title: zucchini jam or yellow kind
directions: Boil squash, sugar and lemon
juice for 25 minutes.
Add pineapple and jello.
Mix well.
Pour into jars.
Cover with paraffin and seal.
May add a few drops of food coloring.
Yields approximately 4 pints.
Preparation time is 35 minutes.

title: easy apple spice cake
directions: Mix without mixer.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Ice with Betty Crocker white icing.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Cook ground meat and ground pork in 2 tablespoons peanut oil. Add onions, green peppers and parsley flakes.
Cook down for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Then add bouillon cubes dissolved in 1 cup of water and corn bread (crumbled up).
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: leftover spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter in skillet until tender. Blend in flour.
Stir in milk.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour into casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mustard glazed cucumbers
directions: Servant and master am I:
Servent of those dead, and master of the living.
Through me spirits immortal speak the message that makes the world weep, and laugh, and wonder, and worship.

title: corned beef hash casserole with noodles
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Cube beef and cheese.
Chop onion and add to chicken soup and milk.
Add noodles and mix well.
Put in greased baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: tasty meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef. Chop onion up fine. Add egg. Add meat loaf seasoning mix. Add rolled cracker crumbs. Mix all ingredients together (except soup) and roll into balls. Brown in skillet for about 45 minutes with lid on top. Turn ever so often. When brown, drain grease and add cream of mushroom soup; simmer until brown.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a baking dish.
Remove from oven and mix next 3 ingredients with butter until smooth.
Pour peaches (with syrup) over mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Marinate first 4 ingredients in mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs, beat well.
Mix in peanut butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Using ice cream scoop, drop onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
You will need a very large bowl for mixing this recipe!

title: steak roll supreme
directions: Rub salt and pepper into steak.
Line one side of steak with bacon slices.
Combine onion tops and mushrooms; mound them in a row down the steak (on top of bacon).
Roll like a jelly roll lengthwise and tie with string.
Brown steak, roll on all sides in bacon drippings.
Bake at 250° or 275° for 3 hours.
When done, slice and serve.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Place ribs in large stewer.
Cover with water.
Boil until meat will slip on bone.
Remove from liquid; let dry 30 minutes. Place on baking sheet or pan.
Baste with dark Karo or honey. Place in oven at 350° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Coat with barbecue sauce of your choice.
Put back in oven.
Broil or brown to your liking.

title: slow cooker pumpkin cake
directions: Cream sugars and oil.
Add eggs and pumpkin and mix well. Sift dry ingredients together and add to pumpkin mixture.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured 2 pound coffee can.
Place in slow cooker and cover top of can with half a dozen paper towels.
Place lid on cooker and bake on high (350°) for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours.
Cake is done when toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: date nut squares
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar and vanilla to eggs.
Sift and add flour and baking powder.
Then add salt, nuts and dates. Spread in well-greased pan.
Bake in 325° oven 25 to 30 minutes. Let cool.
Cut into squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well; roll in small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and press out with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: grandma's cranberry salad
directions: Cook berries, water and salt.
Boil.
Add soda; boil 10 minutes.
Add jello, sugar and marshmallows.
Dissolve sugar. Pour in other ingredients.
Let set up.

title: blueberry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into pie crust; top with blueberries.
Chill before serving.

title: creamed ham and eggs
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Smoothly blend in next 5 ingredients.
Add milk; cook and stir over medium heat until smooth and thickened.
Add sliced eggs and cubed ham.
Heat to serving temperature.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet and sour bean salad
directions: Lightly toss beans, celery, onions and green peppers in bowl. Mix sugar, water, vinegar and oil well.
Then pour liquid over vegetables.
Chill overnight.

title: easy red snapper vera cruz
directions: Rinse snapper fillets, pat dry with paper towels.
Place fillets in a large glass baking dish or pan.
Season the fish with salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Heat olive oil in large skillet until hot over medium-high heat.
Add the onion, green, red and yellow peppers, tomatoes, oregano and garlic.
Cook and stir until vegetables are tender.
Add the bay leaf, olives, lime juice, white wine and jalapeno.
Stir to combine vegetables.
Pour vegetable mixture over fish and season with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350 until fish flakes easily, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cilantro.
Serve with white or yellow rice.

title: angel cookies
directions: Mix all together, and roll dough into small balls.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: country fried steak
directions: Salt and pepper cubed steak.
Dredge in flour.
Brown steak in hot oil in frying pan.
Remove to large dish with cover that can be put in oven.
Saute onion soup mix and fresh onion in frying pan used to brown steak until onion is soft.
Add flour and continue to saute and stir until flour is dark brown.
Add water to make as much gravy as desired.
Pour gravy over steak and cover.
Place in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: nut ball cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 45 minutes.
Let cookies cool completely (even overnight).
Shake in 10x sugar.
Yields 76.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Stir well. Add 1 cup pecans. Stir again. Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until center is cooked, in a buttered casserole dish.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Put 1/4 cup sugar in Miracle Whip.
Toss all ingredients with Miracle Whip.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: oven pork chops
directions: Pan-fry pork chops with salt and pepper only, then put meat, onions, pepper, tomatoes, paste and sugar in roaster pan and cover.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour or until meat is well done.
Serve over noodles or cooked rice.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Place 1/2 cup white sugar in a thick skillet and melt; in the meantime, mix milk, 2 cups sugar, butter and beaten egg.
Cook over moderate heat and stir.
When boiling, add melted sugar.
Cook until soft ball stage, then add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat and spread.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups together, then mix with beaten eggs.
Mix rest of ingredients in. Place in casserole.
Save Ritz crackers and crush them, then mix with the 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Drain fruit and cut orange slices in small pieces.
(Be sure and drain fruit in advance).
Add 1 cup of cold water to jello and fold in sherbet.
Chill until thick and partially set.
Fold in the fruit.
And last, fold in the Cool Whip very gently until smooth.

title: barbecued wax beans
directions: Make a sauce of the first 5 ingredients. Add drained beans and place in casserole. Dice the bacon and sprinkle over top of bean mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly and bacon is crisp.
Fold bacon into beans just before serving.

title: tuna and rice casserole
directions: Microwave cream cheese in a 2-quart glass dish for 20 to 25 seconds, or until softened.
Blend in soup.
Stir in rice, tuna, mushrooms, onion, parsley and pepper.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes; stir to mix.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika. Microwave for 4 to 6 minutes, or until heated through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cocoa mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add mayonnaise, water and vanilla.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Frost.

title: turkey hawaiian
directions: Saute green pepper and garlic in oil until tender.
Blend in soup and pineapple juice.
Add turkey, pineapple tidbits and soy sauce.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot rice and top with slivered almonds.

title: low-fat chicken and vegetables
directions: Brown chicken and oil in a large skillet.
When chicken is almost done, add all vegetables.
Stir and cook until vegetables are cooked but still crisp.
Add 1 cup water, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mexican wedding rings
directions: Cream butter and flour.
Then add sugar, vanilla, salt and nuts.
Make into small balls and press with fork.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and drain; add cheese while mashing potatoes. Saute onions in oleo.
Cook lasagna noodles and drain.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan or dish, layer noodles, mashed potatoes and a little onion and oleo until all is used, the last layer is noodles.
Put rest of onions and oleo on top and bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: foolproof pie crust(anyone can make pie crust.)
directions: In a bowl, mash graham crackers and mix with sugar and cinnamon.
Blend in butter and press into a 9-inch pie pan. Chill until ready to fill.

title: rhubarb-black cherry pie
directions: In mixing bowl, combine rhubarb, black cherries, sugar, tapioca and food coloring.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Line pie plate with pastry; pour in filling.
Add lattice top and seal and flute edges.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cover edges of pastry with foil if browning too quickly.

title: fish and rice
directions: Cook onion in 2 tablespoons butter until slightly tender; stir into rice.
Mix in lemon juice, egg and a dash of salt.
Place half of the fillets in a buttered baking dish; season with salt and pepper.
Top with rice mixture, then remaining fillets.
Brush with remaining butter. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, eggs, cocoa, vanilla, salt and milk.
Mix in blender or slow mixer.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Melt the caramels with margarine and water in top of a double boiler. Stir occasionally until smooth. Combine sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add well beaten eggs and caramel sauce gradually. Mix well. Stir in pecans and pour into pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix ingredients; pour over cabbage.

title: apple and cheese snack
directions: Cut Cheddar into square slices (6).
Then cut the squares into triangles (12).
You do this by cutting each square in half from corner to corner diagonally.
Slice the apple in sixths and cut out the seeds.
Cut each slice across into three triangles.
Layer them, apple, cheese, apple, cheese, apple.
Put a grape on top and hold together with a toothpick.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Beat molasses and egg.
Mix ingredients.
Roll out batter and cut to desired size cookies.
Bake at 400° for about 2 to 3 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and shred meat.
Drain Veg-All.
Mix chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup, chicken and Veg-All with 1/2 cup milk.
Mix well.

title: spicy micro chops
directions: Trim chops of excess fat.
Combine oil and garlic in dish (microwave); spread evenly.
Microwave on High for 1 minute. Combine sherry, soy sauce, brown sugar and pepper in bowl; add pork chops to dish, turning over in garlic oil.
Pour sauce mixture over chops.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes. Turn chops and dish; microwave 2 more minutes.
Keep covered. Microwave at Medium for 12 to 15 minutes until tender and pink color is gone.
Remove to serving dish.
Dissolve cornstarch in water; stir in pan juices and microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes until thick, leave uncovered.
Stir once and pour over chops and serve.

title: blueberry salad delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-Os in water.
Stir in pineapple, pie filling and pecans.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel or half cucumbers and slice them thinly.
Add finely chopped onion to cucumbers with vinegar, salt and pepper.
If too sour, add sugar.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Place in pie shell.
Spread onion and cheese over hamburger.
Mix salt, pepper, catsup and water. Pour over hamburger mixture.
Cover with second pie shell.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: spinach roll(superb tasting and beautiful to serve)
directions: Butter a 10 x 15-inch pan and line with buttered foil. Sprinkle foil with bread crumbs.
In a bowl, combine cooked spinach, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Stir in 6 tablespoons butter. Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat egg whites until they form soft peaks and fold into spinach mixture.
Spoon mixture into prepared pan, spreading gently into a thin layer.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until sides pull away from pan.
Remove from oven and let stand a few minutes. Cover with buttered foil and invert pan.
Remove pan and pull off foil.
Use a spatula if spinach sticks a little. Spread with mushrooms that have been sauteed in 2 tablespoons butter. Sprinkle with Swiss cheese.
Roll up in jelly roll fashion. Sprinkle top with a little grated Swiss cheese.
Serves 8.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Put in bottom of Pyrex dish, not on sides, just bottom.
Beat sugar, egg and butter until mixed well.
Put on top of graham cracker layer.
Put bananas and crushed pineapple on top of butter-sugar mixture.
Mix in layers and let set before adding each layer.
This is better if it sets for 3 or 4 hours before serving.
Must be refrigerated.

title: apricot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Generously spray Pam in Bundt cake pan. Beat with electric mixer for 2 minutes:
cake mix, granulated sugar, eggs, oil and 1 cup apricot nectar.
Pour into cake pan and bake for 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown.
Take cake out of oven (leave oven turned on).
Allow to cool for 15 minutes. During that cooling time, beat together butter, 1/2 cup apricot nectar and powdered sugar.
When 15 minutes cooling time is up, pour liquid over cake and bake for another 15 minutes.
Allow cake to cool 10 to 15 minutes and then carefully remove from pan.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Add sugar gradually, continuing to cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add in 2 additions; beat well after each addition.
Wrap dough in aluminum foil; chill several hours or overnight.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness on lightly floured board.
Cut into desired shapes with floured cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush tops with slightly beaten egg white.
Sprinkle with sugar or top with minced nuts, colored sugar, tiny colored candies, strips of gum drops, diced candied cherries or raisins.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in moderate oven at 375°.
Yields 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: mexican chicken casserole(it's hot)
directions: Mix chicken, onion and chili peppers.
Mix together soup, taco sauce, chips and cheese.
Mix together in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven. Serves 8 to 10.
Sprinkle top with some chips and cheese.

title: chocolate pudding(4 servings)
directions: Blend dry ingredients.
Slowly add milk and eggs.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickens and boils.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Take off from heat and stir in vanilla.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Drain oranges and add enough water to juice to make 1 cup liquid per cake directions.
Add 3 eggs, oil and liquid to cake mix per directions on package.
Add oranges to batter and beat. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan per cake mix directions.

title: chicken paprikish
directions: Brown onion and celery in oleo until tender.
Add salt, paprika and pepper.
Add chicken and brown about 10 minutes. Cover with water and cook 45 minutes.
Make paste of sour cream and flour.
Add and stir until it comes to a boil.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix in top of double boiler the brown sugar and cornstarch. Mix the egg yolks and milk together well.
Add milk and egg mixture to sugar mixture.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cook over boiling water until thick.
Stir constantly, scrapping sides often.
Place in cooked pie shell.
Cover with meringue.

title: cousin clara's beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into 1/4 to 1/2-inch chunks.
Brown in 3 tablespoons butter or oleo. When thoroughly brown, add 2/3 cup water and let simmer until tender.
Add mushrooms, cream of mushroom soup and onion soup mix.
(I add the water on the mushrooms, too.)
Blend sour cream and flour to a smooth consistency and add to mixture just before serving.
Serve on rice or noodles.
Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: potato pancake
directions: Mix potatoes, salt, fat and flour.
Bake until brown or you can fry.

title: romaine lettuce salad
directions: Put lettuce in salad bowl and sprinkle with all other ingredients.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Serve with dressing.

title: carrot soup
directions: In a
heavy
3 to 4 quart saucepan melt the butter over moderate heat.
Stir in the onion and cook, stirring occasionally for
minutes
or
until they are soft but not browned. Add the carrots,
chicken
stock,
tomato
paste and rice and simmer gently,
uncovered,
for
minutes.
Puree the soup through a blender
or
food
processor
and return mixture to saucepan. Season
with
salt and white pepper and stir in the cream (milk).

title: toothpaste putty(it's stretchy)
directions: Will need small dish and powdered pencil lead (optional).

title: creole tomato sauce(southern)
directions: Saute onion
and
pepper in butter over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add
rest
of ingredients and simmer for 1 hour over low heat.
Thicken, if desired.

title: downhome apple pie
directions: Place one unbaked pie crust in pie plate.
Mix all ingredients and heap in pie plate. Cover with second pie crust, removed from store tin.
Press top and bottom crusts together with tines of fork or your favorite fluting technique. Cut several small slits for steam to escape.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes. Check for doneness by piercing apples through a slit.
Cool before slicing. Yields 6 slices.

title: fat-free pumpkin sheet cake
directions: Blend dry cake mix and pumpkin pie filling with wire whisk. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 28 to 30 minutes.

title: hot tomato relish
directions: Measure bell peppers and onions after grinding.
Peel tomatoes, cut up and press into a measuring cup to get 1 gallon. Cook tomatoes until tender, add other ingredients and cook until thick.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all together. Chill and serve!

title: muddy buddies
directions: Kids love to help.

title: refrigerator bread and butter pickles
directions: Heat first 6 ingredients until well dissolved; let cool.
Add enough fresh cucumber slices and onions to make 7 cups.
Mix thoroughly and put in clean sterilized jars.
Place in refrigerator for 1 day and 1 night before eating.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Add next 2 ingredients. Mix together flour and oatmeal.
After measuring oatmeal, put a small amount into blender and process until powder forms.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Mix together all these ingredients.
Add chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and nuts.
Make golf ball size balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: cream cheese, cranberry, pepper spread
directions: Thoroughly mix cranberry sauce and pepper jelly. Place cream cheese on small plate or in shallow bowl. Pour cranberry/jelly mixture over cream cheese. Place container with cream cheese mixture in center of large serving plate. Arrange crackers on platter around cream cheese mixture. Be sure to provide small knives for spreading cream cheese on crackers.

title: ms. mary's asparagus casserole
directions: Make a sauce, mixing mayonnaise, lemon juice and your choice of soup together.
Layer dish with asparagus, then peas.
Cover these with the sauce.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs and nuts on top. Bake in 325° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: jim's rice custard
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Mix together with remaining ingredients and pour into a buttered casserole.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Set the bowl in a big pan of hot water.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: silly slime
directions: You will need 1 large bowl, 1 measuring cup, rubber gloves, 2 small bowls, 2 spoons, straws and plastic bags.

title: bacon, cheddar and potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into small cubes.
Microwave potatoes for about 7 to 8 minutes.
Put potatoes in glass casserole dish. Put finely chopped onion over potatoes.
Crumble bacon over onion and potatoes.
Grate cheese and pour mixture.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: impossible bisquick cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch pie pan.
Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain and stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pan.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth.
Pour into pan. Bake 35 minutes.
Top with 2 sliced tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife comes out clean, 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: monterey casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions and seasoning.
Drain.
Add beans, soup and Ro-Tel; mix well.

title: chicken a la cream
directions: Wash beef and dry with paper towel.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish line pan with beef, then place chicken, wrapped with bacon; salt and pepper to taste.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: domates me feta(stuffed tomatoes with feta cheese)
directions: Cut the tops off the tomatoes. Scoop out the insides and set aside.
Discard seeds, but keep the pulp.
Preheat the oven to 350°.
Coarsely chop the pulp and combine scallions, parsley, Feta, bread crumbs and olive oil.
Spoon mixture into hollowed out tomatoes.
Place tomatoes, right side up, in an 8 x 8-inch pan and bake 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook the fettucini noodles in boiling water (follow box directions). Saute garlic in melted butter. Add light cream, Parmesan cheese and egg yolk to butter. Stir until ingredients blend together. Drain noodles.
Pour sauce over noodles and toss together. Serve immediately.

title: barbecued flank steak
directions: Mix marinade ingredients together well.
Pour over flank steak.
Cover; let stand in the refrigerator for 24 hours.
Remove from marinade; cook outside on your grill, or broil in your oven. Serves 4.

title: stewed corn
directions: Cook corn and water until done.
Add salt, pepper, sugar and margarine. Then add flour mixture to desired thickness.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onion in the margarine and oil in a large heavy bottomed skillet, covered, for 15 minutes on low heat.
Uncover pan. Add salt and sugar. Raise to a moderate heat.

Cook for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring often enough so onions do not burn. Sprinkle with 15 tablespoons flour, slowly, so it does not burn (taking at least 3 minutes to add). Add the rest of the ingredients.
Season with fresh garlic and seasoned salt. Simmer for another 15 minutes. Serves a very large group.

title: tackett's cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients according to cake mix directions and bake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Drain pineapple before using.
Mix rest of ingredients well and spread over cooled cake.

title: spicy pork tenderloin
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; rub over tenderloins.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 4 hours.
Grill over hot coals 15 minutes per side or until juices run clear.
Makes 8 servings.

title: three potato soup
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a saucepan.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Do not drain.
Mash vegetables slightly.
Stir in milk, butter, parsley flakes and pepper.
Heat.
Garnish with green onions, if desired.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Fry hamburger with onions.
Drain.
Add taco sauce.
Put hamburger in pie pan.
Mix milk, eggs and Bisquick in bowl.
Pour over hamburger; top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Top with lettuce, tomatoes and sour cream.

title: cheesy california blend
directions: Spray pan with Pam to prevent sticking.
Sprinkle French fried onions on top and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Break egg into a cup and beat.
Add vinegar and enough water to fill the cup. Sift flour with salt; cut shortening into flour until it forms pea size particles. Add liquid and mix well.
Roll out dough (one crust at a time) on lightly floured surface.
Makes 5 to 6 single pie crusts.
Keeps for days refrigerated.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: judy's cherry brownie cupcakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Empty a box of fudge brownie mix (family size) into large mixer bowl.
Add eggs and 1/3 cup of water.
Beat 1 minute.
Add 1/3 cup more water and beat 1 minute.
Stir in one cup whole maraschino cherries, then 1/2 cup in halves.
Bake in paper cup lined muffin tin for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: apple slaw
directions: Chop cabbage.
Add to large bowl, cabbage, apple, raisins, celery and nuts (pecans, walnuts or peanuts).
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add vinegar and mayonnaise; mix together.
Can serve immediately or chill a couple of hours before serving. Serves 4.

title: butter tarts
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and butter as for pie dough. Add milk and slightly beaten egg.
Work in sugar after dough is made (last of all).
This helps to make dough keep its shape.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream cheese and vegetable
oil.
Add
salt,
soda
and pepper to sifted flour.
Add
slowly until all dry ingredients are mixed well.
Press out
with electric cookie press or make balls and press on pan.
Bake
on
ungreased	baking	sheet at 300° for about 30 minutes
or
until firm, but not brown.
Cut into desired size as soon as you remove from oven.

title: chicken chili
directions: Saute chicken breasts in butter until done.
Boil tomatoes, picante sauce and water; reduce heat and simmer about 45 minutes. Spoon into bowls.
Add cheese, if desired.

title: cheese egg puff
directions: Make the night before.
Beat eggs.
Blend in cheese and remaining ingredients.
Store in Tupperware in refrigerator.
When ready to bake, pour in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: shrimp and crab casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except crumbs.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry burst pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Mix well. Add next 4 ingredients. Mix well. Pour into pie crusts. Freeze for 2 to 3 hours. Let stand at room temperature for 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: bean and cabbage soup
directions: Rinse and drain soaked beans. In a large pot, heat the olive oil over medium heat. Add the onion and garlic and cook for 7 minutes, stirring often, until soft. Add oregano and thyme and stir for 30 seconds to release the flavors. Add chicken broth, water and beans; cover and bring to boil over high heat. Reduce heat to medium-low, simmer for 45 minutes or until beans are nearly tender. Meanwhile, cut potatoes into 1/2 inch chunks, coarsely chop cabbage and dice carrots. Add vegetables, salt and pepper to beans. Bring soup back to a boil over medium-high heat. Reduce heat to medium-low; cover and simmer an additional 35 minutes or until vegetables are very tender. Remove pot from heat and with a slotted spoon, mash some of the beans and vegetables to make soup thicker. Serve with french bread and fresh lettuce salad.

title: cheddar cheese dip
directions: Fry hamburger and drain.
Mix cheese soup, salsa and hamburger in a bowl and serve.

title: taco crunch
directions: Brown hamburger with onion. Drain grease. Add enchilada sauce, beans and corn (drained). Put on top of tortilla chips on plate. Add lettuce, cheese, tomatoes and sour cream.

title: relish-rinn
directions: Put in glass jar and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Use large Tupperware bowl.
Sift coca and sugar together in bowl.
Place butter on top and add milk.
Microwave on high for 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in buttered 8x8 inch dish.

title: pork chops
directions: Mix bread crumbs and cheese in a food storage bag.
Add pork chops and shake until they are well coated.
Add a little oil to your
skillet
or
griddle
and cook until done.
Sooo easy!

title: doughnuts
directions: Heat oil to 375°.
Mix flour, sugar, milk, vanilla and spices until well blended.
Turn dough onto floured surface and knead about 10 minutes.
Roll out to about 3/8-inch thick.
Cut with a floured doughnut cutter.
Drop into hot oil and fry until brown on both sides.
Remove and drain.
To coat, drop one at a time in a small paper bag containing powdered sugar and shake.

title: easy sugar cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook and stir until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with cinnamon or nutmeg.

title: french coconut custard pie
directions: With mixer, blend eggs first until fluffy.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: yummy bars
directions: Combine cake mix with 1/3 cup of milk and 3/4 cup melted butter.
Put half of mix in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream Crisco
and sugar well.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing after each addition. Add flavor,
zucchini,	nuts, raisins and sour cream.
Now add flour mixture;
mix
well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake in
preheated	oven
at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Turn out of pan on rack.
Cool.
Cooling in refrigerator makes easier slicing.

title: "fly off the plate" hot cakes
directions: Mix the ingredients; fry on griddle.
Butter each hot cake and serve with your favorite syrups.

title: lacy oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter in a bowl.
Cool. Put oatmeal and sugar in with butter; add egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoonful on foil.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cookies will spread out flat.
Let cool on foil before removing.

title: orange cheese salad
directions: Bring pineapple and water to boil. Dissolve Jell-O in hot mixture. Cool until consistency of egg whites. Add cheese and nuts. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into individual salad molds or one large mold. Refrigerate until set.

title: banana soup
directions: Chop up a banana and put it in a bowl.
Pour milk over the banana.
Put some sugar on it.
You can eat it for breakfast or for a snack.
Some kids put corn flakes in it.

title: cole slaw
directions: Wash and drain cole slaw mix.
Mix all other ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour over slaw mix and toss until completely mixed.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil; boil 5 minutes.
Add soda and stir.
Pour over 15 cups popped corn.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring often.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Cut core out of cabbage.
Place core-side down into large pot of boiling, slightly salted water until leaves loosen.
Remove to rack for cooling.
Meanwhile, dice salt pork and saute until crisp. Add diced onion and saute for a few minutes.
Add to rice and meat mixture, salt and pepper to taste and mix with fork gently, but well.
Place heaping tablespoonful of mixture in a cabbage leaf, fold sides and roll over leaf to completely encase mixture.
Line roasting pan with cabbage leaves or a little tomato soup.
Place stuffed cabbages in covered pan.
Bake on medium temperature for about 1 hour; add more tomato soup and bake for another hour until done.
Canned, chopped tomatoes may be used.
Yields 35 to 40.

title: best corn relish
directions: Boil the corn 5 minutes and then cut from the cob.
Combine with remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Seal in canning jars.

title: microwave divinity
directions: In a 4-cup glass measure or bowl, mix sugar, water and vinegar.
Place plastic wrap on top; poke holes in plastic. Microwave 12 to 17 minutes on Medium-high.
Test after 10 minutes. (A few drops in cold water should form into a soft ball.)
Set aside.
Beat until stiff, but not until peaks.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix the sour cream, Miracle Whip, mustard, vinegar and sugar. Chill.
Chop the eggs, celery, carrots, onion and pepper.
Combine everything with the macaroni.
Best prepared 1 day ahead.

title: weight watchers soup
directions: Cook until tender, about 40 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Beat for 7 minutes in double boiler until beaters leave holes in frosting.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place each piece of chicken between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Top each with a piece of ham and 3 tablespoons of Mozzarella cheese.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Tuck in sides and secure each roll with wooden picks.

title: homemade rotel dip
directions: Mix or blend all ingredients together.
Chill and serve with favorite chips.

title: nutty cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine the cream cheese and butter.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Go buy them.
Then you scrape them when you get home.
Then you wash them, then you cut them.
You wash them two times and then you cook them.
You put oil in pan, then put the carrots.
Then you take them out.
Then you eat them.

title: almond bark fudge
directions: Butter an 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Separate candy coating into squares if necessary.
Heat candy coating and milk over low heat, stirring occasionally, until coating is melted and mixture is smooth, about 5 minutes; remove from heat.
Stir in almonds and almond extract.
Spread in pan.
Garnish with additional almonds or cherries, if desired.
Refrigerate until firm, about 1 1/2 hours.
Cut into about 1-inch squares, about 36 candy pieces.

title: chicken pot pies
directions: Mix everything together.
Pour into slightly baked pie shells. Top with unbaked pie shell.
Make a few slits in top.
Bake at 375° until pie shells are golden brown.

title: rotmos(swedish rutabaga)
directions: Peel, cut up and cook rutabaga in small amount of water.
Do the same with the potatoes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Toss together and place in jars or other container.
Allow at least 24 hours storing time so that flavors will combine.

title: ham loaf
directions: Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Add 1/2 cup water to pan while baking.
Reserve 1/2 cup of basting ingredients to serve.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all vegetables in a shallow baking dish.
Heat broth and add oil, garlic, salt, bay leaf, savory and tarragon (dried herbs should be crushed fine). Bring broth mixture to a boil. Pour over vegetables and cover casserole.
Lid must fit tightly or cover with foil.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Gently mix vegetables twice during cooking.
At end of cooking time, uncover casserole and sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese. Cover completely with sliced Jack cheese.
Place back in hot oven until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: frosted ribbon loaf
directions: Trim crusts from loaf of bread.
Slice bread lengthwise 3 equal layers.
Bottom layer spread ham salad.
Second layer spread with egg salad.
Wrap in foil and chill.

title: mexican crepes
directions: Roll ham, cheese and chiles in tortillas and place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: bok choy sensational salad
directions: Wash, core, and chop the bok choy and onions into bite-size pieces.
Chill after drying.

title: hot potato rolls
directions: Pour scalded milk into a big bowl and add Spudflakes, sugar, oil and eggs.
Stir until smooth.
Add 2 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Stir in yeast.
Add enough more flour to make a soft dough.

Turn out on lightly floured board and knead until smooth. Place in a greased bowl and lightly grease the top of the dough. Cover and let rise in a warm place until light and doubled (about 1 1/2 hours).
When light, punch down and let rest 10 minutes.
Shape dough into rolls or coffee cakes, let rise until doubled (about 45 minutes).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes for pan rolls or coffee cakes, 15 to 20 minutes for rolls on a baking sheet.

title: pasta al pesto
directions: Grind the first 6 ingredients fine in blender.
Add oil, small amount at a time, stirring to form thick sauce.
Keep at room temperature. Cook noodles only until firm.
Spoon pesto on noodles.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients and set aside.
Put chopped zucchini in blender with eggs and oil.
Blend until smooth, then add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Add this to other ingredients. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° 1 hour or more until done.

title: pig picken cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into 2 pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp pie
directions: Add the ingredients in layers in a 9 x 13-inch dish: apples, sprinkle cinnamon over apples, add sugar and cake mix.
Cover mixture with margarine slices.
Pour 1 cup of water over top. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: floating island
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and salt and add to milk.
Put in a double boiler over low heat.
Stir constantly.
When mixture forms a thin coat on a spoon, empty immediately in a large bowl as large as a mixing bowl.
Add vanilla immediately.
Make meringue by beating the 2 reserved whites and adding 2 tablespoons sugar. Drop by tablespoonfuls on top for "floating islands."
Chill and serve.

title: fat free chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, milk, applesauce, vinegar and vanilla.
Beat at low speed of electric beater until blended.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Can be served with Cool Whip or decorated anyway you wish.
The plain cake makes 12 squares.

title: baked eggs
directions: Cut crust off bread.
Melt butter; dip bread in butter.
Cool. Put in a muffin pan and form a crust in pan.
Brown 15 or 20 minutes at 350°.
Drop eggs in each muffin.
Return to oven.
Cook approximately 15 minutes more.
Sprinkle before done with seasoned salt.

title: hamburger-biscuit casserole
directions: Cook meat, onion and celery.
Drain.
Stir in flour, tomato sauce, seasonings and peas.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and top with biscuits and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are golden.

title: senator edward m. kennedy's cape cod fish chowder
directions: Simmer haddock in 2 cups of water for 15 minutes.
Drain off and reserve the broth.
Remove the skin and bones from the fish. Saute the diced salt pork in a large pot until crisp.
Remove the salt pork and saute the onions in the fat until golden brown.
Add fish, celery, potatoes and bay leaf.
Measure reserve fish broth plus enough boiling water to make 3 cups liquid.
Add to pot and simmer 40 minutes.
Add milk and butter and simmer for an additional 5 minutes, or until well heated.
Season with salt and pepper.
Makes 8 servings.

title: creamy mexican chocolate iced coffee
directions: Whip 1/2 cup of the whipping cream to soft peaks; set aside. In a pitcher or bowl, combine remaining 1/2 cup cream with chocolate syrup, sugar and cinnamon.
Stir in coffee until sugar dissolves.
Fill four glasses with ice; pour coffee mixture over ice.
Top with whipped cream and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: layered taco salad
directions: Layer chopped lettuce and then chopped green onions, tomatoes, chopped chili hot beans and cheese.
Crush chips on top, then add bottle of dressing and toss.
Serve with chips.

title: scott's low-fat tuna salad
directions: Mix ingredients; add dressing to taste.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Combine and microwave sugar, Karo syrup and water.
Beat whites until stiff, with salt.
Pour hot syrup mix over egg whites, beating constantly until stiff and dull.
Fold in vanilla and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Cool.
Enjoy.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, onions, celery, salt, pepper and garlic salt together.
Place in casserole dish. Cover top of meat mixture with mushroom and chicken soups.
Cover top of soups with Tater Tots. Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry mincemeat salad
directions: Prepare mincemeat as for pie.
Mix both packages jello with boiling water.
Add lemon juice, mix with mincemeat mixture and cool.
When jello mixture begins to set, add celery and nut meats (if desired).
Pour in mold.
Serve with mayonnaise sprinkled with paprika.
This is good anytime!

title: grandma's apple dapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: raisin oat cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt, baking soda and oats.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins. Drop by spoonfuls on baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: corn and red pepper soup
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt butter and add bell pepper and onion; cook until crisp but tender.
Add chicken broth, corn and cumin. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce to low heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes or until corn is tender.
Pour into blender and process until smooth.
Return to pan and whisk in sour cream until blended.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Reheat, but do not boil.
Garnish with sunflower seeds.
Serves 4.

title: brownie meringues
directions: Beat egg whites with salt, vinegar and vanilla until soft peaks.
Gradually add sugar, beating to stiff peaks.
Fold in nuts and chocolate.
Drop by rounded teaspoons on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix until you get dough.

title: dressing
directions: Grease pan lightly.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix well sugar, eggs, flour and milk.
Cook slightly and cool. Add whipping cream, Carnation milk and salt.
Finish container with white milk.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Cook sugar in boiling water until it thickens in cold water. Pour it over egg whites.
Beat steady.
Add chocolate.
Add vanilla; beat until stiff enough to spread on cake.

title: spicy short ribs
directions: Dust ribs with flour; brown in vegetable shortening in large skillet.
Pour off excess fat.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over ribs.
Cook under low heat 2 1/2 hours or until ribs are tender.
Turn ribs and baste with sauce often.

title: crab appetizer
directions: The day before serving combine all ingredients.
In summer serve cold in individual shells.
Also, nice as a cold dip; or hot in a chafing dish.	Can be used as an entree or as an appetizer on melba toast.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Cut apples and oranges into bite size pieces.
Quarter cherries.
Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.

title: red bean soup
directions: Saute chopped onion and garlic.
Mix all together in crock-pot or saucepan and cook until tender.

title: pizza dough
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Add the rest or the ingredients and mix.
Knead dough.
Let raise about an hour.
Spread the oil on pizza pan.
Roll or spread the dough on the pizza pan.
Cover the dough with your favorite sauce and toppings.
Bake in a hot oven at 450° about 15 minutes or until done.

title: pan-fried eggplant
directions: Halve eggplant lengthwise, then cut crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Combine egg and 1 tablespoon water.
Combine crackers, parsley, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Dip eggplant into egg mixture, then into cracker mixture.
Cook in hot oil until tender and golden (2 to 3 minutes per side).
Drain on paper towel and serve.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Mix Butter Buds according to box. Pour mix over potatoes in a microwave-safe dish.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients according to taste.
Top with a package of Butter Buds dry mix.
Microwave until potatoes are tender.
Stir occasionally to ensure seasoning is throughout.

title: no fail chocolate cupcakes
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl together and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 18 cupcakes.

title: taco shells
directions: Beat until runny.
Fry in just very little grease.
Flatten as much as possible.

title: cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Melt oleo; add cake mix, egg and pecans. Mix well by hand. Press into 9 x 13 glass dish.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Separate eggs; beat whites until stiff but not dry, then add sugar and corn syrup.
Add egg yolks, salt and vanilla and beat until mixed.
Whip the cream until thick but not stiff and fold into egg mixture.
Pour into ice cube tray.
Wet bottom of tray and freeze in freezer compartment.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add onion, green peppers, mushrooms, tomato sauce, sugar, salt and pepper to taste, olives, Italian seasoning and pepperoni.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add 4 ounces Cheddar cheese.
Blend in macaroni.
Put in baking dish and top with Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Layer the first 3 ingredients in a 13 x 9 baking dish, starting with the sauerkraut, then the corned beef and last, the cheese.
Set aside while preparing the sauce.

title: quick chicken bake
directions: Mix together and place in a buttered 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes.
If you prefer cream of mushroom soup or Cheddar cheese soup, go for it.

title: little porkies
directions: Brown diced pork in Dutch oven.
Add mushroom soup; stir well. Bake on low for 45 minutes.
Top with mushrooms.
Mix up stuffing according to package directions.
Place on top of mushrooms and sauce.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes longer on low.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion, then add chili powder, cumin and cream of mushroom soup.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Layer with beans, tortilla chips (broken into pieces), cheese, Ro-Tel and black olives.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and warmed.

title: crusty tuna pie(4 to 6 servings)
directions: In a saucepan, combine the potatoes, carrots, onion, parsley, salt, pepper, water and tuna.
Cover and boil slowly for 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in soup; pour into greased casserole dish.
Cover with buttered bread triangles. Bake in a hot oven at 400° until lightly browned.

title: strawberry smoothie
directions: Place the fruit, yogurt and vanilla in a food processor (or blender). Run until smooth. Add the ice and run until smooth. Serve cold. Serves 2 to 3.

title: sausage and vegetable jambalaya
directions: Put everything together in rice cooker and cook.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together. Cut in butter or shortening with pastry blender until mixture is like coarse cornmeal. Store in covered container in refrigerator until needed.

title: orange sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in a 10-inch skillet. Stir in frozen orange juice, water, butter and grated orange rind. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; simmer 2 minutes.
Set aside.
Prepare dumplings.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Saute onions in shortening until transparent.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Simmer slowly until well blended. Add cheese.
Melt on low heat; serve over warmer.
Serve with green vegetables or chips.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package and drain well.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on low heat until thoroughly heated.

title: lady baltimore cake
directions: Stir shortening to soften.
Gradually add sugar and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add extracts and egg yolks. Sift flour; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and water, beginning and ending with flour.
Beat after each addition. Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp with cashew nuts
directions: Marinate shrimp meat in a mixture of egg white, cornstarch and 1/2 teaspoon salt for a least 20 minutes.
Fry cashew nuts in hot oil until browned.
Set aside.
Fry marinated shrimp in hot oil until pink.
Drain and set aside.
Saute green onion and ginger until soft.
Add shrimp.
Season with rice wine, 1/2 teaspoon salt and sesame oil.
Add cashew nuts.
Stir-fry for 1 minute.

title: peanut fruit slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients, except peanuts and marshmallows. Toss lightly and chill.
Just before serving, fold in peanuts and marshmallows.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli and drain.
In bowl, add all other ingredients, except crackers and butter.
Place broccoli and ingredients in casserole dish.
Cover with crushed crackers and margarine, mixed together.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: easy au gratin potatoes
directions: Slice peeled potatoes crosswise 1/4-inch thick.
Cook for approximately 10 to 12 minutes or until slightly tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain.
In skillet, melt butter.
Add flour and salt. Stir over medium heat for 1 1/2 minutes.
Slowly add milk while stirring.
Add Velveeta cheese in small cubes.
Melt cheese thoroughly.
Pour sauce over drained potatoes in glass baking dish.
Heat in 350° preheated oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Add chocolate to milk and place over low flame.
Bring to a boil and cook until mixture is smooth.
Add sugar and syrup; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Let boil slowly until mixture is desired thickness.
Add vanilla.
Serve hot on ice cream, or with fondue.
Makes 1 1/3 cups sauce.

title: potato and tuna casserole
directions: Heat butter in saucepan and saute onion about 5 minutes, until golden brown.
Blend in flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in tuna.
Remove from heat.

title: onion rings
directions: Peel onions and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Separate into rings.
Heat 1 inch of oil in a 3-quart saucepan to 375°.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Dip each ring into batter, letting excess drip into bowl.
Fry a few at a time in hot oil, turning once until golden brown, about 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Keep warm in 300° oven until ready to serve.

title: italian turkey dressing
directions: Poke holes in wrapper of French bread and let sit 3 days. Cube.
Grind all ingredients except mushrooms.
Saute in butter. Mix well with cubed bread.
Add poultry seasoning to taste.
Stuff turkey in usual manner.

title: hot ham salad
directions: In a bowl, combine the first six ingredients.
Gently fold in the oranges.
Transfer to a greased 1 1/2 quart baking dish. Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake, uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: perfect apple pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to package directions for 2 crust pie, using 9-inch pie pan.
Heat oven to 425°.

title: terri storter's hot jambalaya
directions: Saute onion, celery and pepper in garlic butter for 2 to 3 minutes or until limp.
Add stock*, tomatoes and spices.
Simmer briskly, uncovered and stirring frequently, for 5 minutes. Mixture will be thickened and reduced.
Add sausage and cook another 2 minutes, until further reduced.
Stir in shelled raw shrimp and cook another 2 minutes until shrimp are barely opaque. Add cooked rice and stir well.
Serve immediately sprinkled with parsley for garnish.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly; add Karo.
Mix sugar and flour and add to eggs and Karo mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; reduce to 300° for about 35 minutes.

title: orange or apricot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in heated pineapple juice.
Add buttermilk, stir well and cool.
Add Cool Whip and pecans.
Refrigerate unti firm.

title: baked quail
directions: Clean birds.
Wipe out inside with damp cloth.
Stuff with dressing of ingredients; season to taste.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook onions and squash until tender.
In buttered casserole, put alternate layers of squash, soup and bread crumbs.
Put margarine on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast sausage gravy
directions: Crumble sausage and onion in large pan.
Saute over medium heat, breaking pieces as they cook.
Cook until sausage is brown. Stir in flour and cook for a minute.
Add hot milk.
Stir until thick.
Add seasonings.
Serve over toast or biscuit.

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill and allow to marinate.

title: beef 'n noodles
directions: Put 3 to 5 pounds of cut up sirloin steak in pressure cooker, cook for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Add
egg noodles and brown gravy mix.
Cook until noodles are done.

title: cheese dream rounds
directions: Spread each round of bread with prepared mustard and heap some of the cheese on each round.
Sprinkle each with salt, pepper, paprika and 1/8 teaspoon of the Worcestershire sauce.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Put in bowl the sugar, flour and cornmeal.
Toss with fork. Add eggs, oleo, lemon juice and milk.
Beat until smooth and thoroughly mixed.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: glue dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and knead like dough.
This dough will harden nicely and can be dampened on the back side and stuck to a bulletin board or gifts.

title: bonbons
directions: Work well with hands and make into small balls.
Chill.
Melt the Parowax and chocolate chips in double boiler.
When dip is hot, place a toothpick in each ball and roll in dip to coat. Place balls on wax paper.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt Hershey bars, marshmallows and milk in a double boiler over simmering water.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream and pour into the baked pie shell.
Chill until set.
Can use graham cracker crust.

title: plum pudding
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add spices, milk and flour; mix well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Steam 1 hour in 9-inch cake pan (I use an electric skillet with 2-inches water and a rack in bottom).
Keep water just hot enough to make steam; cover with lid.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and pulp.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Sift together flour, baking powder and cinnamon; stir into first mixture alternately with buttermilk and cream.
Add butter last.

title: spicy rice
directions: Boil rice in chicken broth.
Saute vegetables in butter.
Mix with rice.
Add salt to taste.

title: dad's favorite(hot fudge pudding cake)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Measure flour, granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Blend in milk and shortening.
Stir in nuts.
Spread into ungreased square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Stir together brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Sprinkle over what is already in bowl.
Gently pour hot water over all.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Serve warm.
Vanilla ice cream over top is a nice touch.
Serves 9, unless Steve is eating!

title: pig cake
directions: Cream cake mix, butter, vanilla and orange juice.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat 4 minutes.
Drain oranges and add to batter. Beat only until blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost.

title: corn timbales
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Stir in corn and green onions (may set aside some corn and green onions for garnish).
Spray 2 (12-ounce) casseroles with nonstick coating.
Divide egg mixture between the two.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate truffle cookies
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Chop unsweetened chocolate.
Cut butter into pieces.
Melt chopped chocolate, butter and one cup chocolate chips in a small pan in oven, stirring occasionally.
Cool.

title: amy's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly with a wire whisk.
Select 3 to 4 pounds meat.
Place meat in the sauce and cook on stove top in a pot 1 to 2 hours.

title: shrimp okra gumbo
directions: To Make Roux:
Stir oil and flour in a cast-iron skillet over medium heat until brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine apples, sugar and water
in large mixing bowl and let stand 10 minutes.
Mix all together and pour into greased and floured 10 x 13-inch pan or use 2 smaller pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cocktail mushrooms
directions: Melt butter; saute garlic slowly.
Let stand a while.
Remove garlic and add drained (or fresh) mushrooms, thyme, oregano and saute over low heat until lightly browned.
Turn off heat and let stand all day to season, stirring occasionally.
If time permits, reheat before transfering to chafing dish or candle warmer.
Add lots of grated Parmesan cheese; toss lightly to distribute cheese.

title: maxine's "7-up" cake
directions: All ingredients should be at room temperature.
Using butter, grease and flour 1 tube cake pan.
Set oven to 325°.
Cream butter.
Add sugar to butter gradually.
Cream for 5 minutes or until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating batter thoroughly after each addition.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Add flour alternately with 7-Up brand soda.
Mix thoroughly but gently and pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cream cheese; whip cream cheese, peanut butter and Cool Whip.
Add powdered sugar and milk.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into crust.
Freeze for about 3 hours.
Serve topped with chocolate syrup or whipped cream.

title: pizza cookies
directions: Beat together margarine, peanut butter, and sugars until light and fluffy; blend in eggs.
Add combined flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats and 1/3 cup candies.

title: superburgers
directions: Brown meat in skillet and drain.
Add garlic, onion and salt; cook 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer about 20 minutes, or until thick.
Serve on bun.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix and pour into vanilla wafer pie crust.
Grate Hershey bar on top.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, pumpkin and vanilla.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Add almonds and chips; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: apple nut torte
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add in flour, baking soda, cinnamon, apples, walnuts and a touch of salt.
Mix all ingredients well and spoon into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for an hour.

title: window cleaner
directions: This makes 1 gallon.
Put in gallon jug and fill with water.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook hen until tender (be sure to salt well).
Let cool and cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Take 1 cup of the rich broth and cook onion in it until tender.
Add the tomato sauce and mushroom soup to the onion broth.
Cook spaghetti in remaining chicken broth until tender.
Drain spaghetti and add tomato sauce, onion, mushroom soup and chicken pieces to the spaghetti.
Then add the pimento.
Cook in a 350° oven until hot through and through, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Place carrots in casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients cover.
Bake at 375 degrees for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pecan chicken
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine flour, pecans, sesame seed, paprika, salt and pepper.
Combine egg and buttermilk.
Dip chicken in egg mix.
Dredge in flour mix.
Place chicken in casserole; turn once in butter.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Melt 2 Tbsp. margarine in layer cake pan. Mix above ingredients together and put on top of melted margarine. Place can of biscuits on top of this mixture. Bake at 350° until biscuits are done. Let cool a little before turning out of pan.

title: quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 3 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients and chill overnight in refrigerator.
Serve with any raw vegetables you like.

title: zucchini-tomato skillet
directions: In large skillet or wok, heat oil.
Add zucchini and stir-fry a few minutes until slightly browned; push to one side of pan. Add onion and garlic to other side of pan; saute until slightly golden.
Sprinkle with basil and stir-fry over low heat until zucchini is crisp-tender.
Gently stir in tomatoes just to heat. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
If desired, sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bubble bread
directions: Mix all ingredients
together, except the last four, in order given.
More flour may
be	needed,
dough should not be sticky to handle.
Form
dough
into walnut-sized balls.
Melt butter (set aside).
In a
small
bowl mix sugar and cinnamon. Dip balls into melted butter,
then roll in mixture.
Place in greased Bundt pan. Add
chopped
nuts,
if desired.
Let rise for 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Empty
pineapple
juice
into
a gallon container.
Add frozen juices
one
at
a time.
Add sugar and Kool-Aid flavor packet. Finally add enough water to make a gallon mixture and stir well. Serve
in
combination
with
ginger ale for a refreshing party drink!

title: old fashioned taffy(from the files of ola dortch williams)
directions: Butter sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Combine sugar, molasses and water.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Then bring to boil; add vinegar and cook to light crack stage (268°).
Remove from heat; add butter and sift in soda. Stir to mix.
Turn out (don't scrape) onto buttered platter or large shallow pan.
For even cooling, use spatula to turn the edges to the center.
Pull taffy while it is as warm as you can handle. Use only finger tips to pull.
Dip fingers in cornstarch if candy sticks.

When candy is light taffy color and gets hard to pull, cut in fourths, pull each piece into long strand, about 1/2-inch thick. With buttered scissors, quickly snip taffy in bite size pieces. Wrap each piece in waxed paper.
Makes 1 1/4 pounds.

title: jalapeno cranberries
directions: Wash and pick over cranberries, discarding any that are crushed or shriveled. Bring 1 cup water to boil and add cranberries and sugar. Continue to boil until all the berries are opened and mixture thickens slightly, stirring often. Turn off heat and cool slightly. Mince peppers and add to the cooled cranberry mixture. Add lemon juice and stir well. Excellent with turkey, chicken or roast pork.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and rise with cold water to cool.
Mix all together and chill.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; squeeze water out of spinach by wrapping in paper towels.
Mix all ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Serve with celery, carrots, nacho chips, Wheat Thins, etc.

title: classic creamy coleslaw
directions: Combine mayonnaise, milk, vinegar, sugar, bell pepper, onions, and pickle relish.
Add black pepper to taste.
Pour all ingredients over coleslaw mix.

title: lynn's sour cream muffins
directions: Mix all together.
Spray small muffin tins well.
Fill completely with batter.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cheddar fish casserole
directions: Place fish in bottom of casserole. Mix all other ingredients together, reserving 1/3 cup of cheese for top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake until cheese bubbles.

title: parmesan orange roughy(microwave)
directions: Cut fish into serving size pieces.
Beat egg with water.
Mix together crumbs, cheese, paprika and pepper on a piece of waxed paper.
Put flour on another piece of waxed paper.
Coat fish with flour; dip into egg mixture and then coat with crumb mixture. Place fish into a shallow microwave dish.
Microwave, uncovered, 5 to 6 minutes, rotating dish once.
Garnish with snipped parsley. Serves 4.

title: chicken caccia taco
directions: Sprinkle chicken with seasoned salt.
Brown in hot oil and drain.
Combine taco mix, water and canned tomatoes.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: lemon pie
directions: In the top of a doubler, mix sugar and flour together. Add beaten egg yolks to mixture, stirring often. Add boiling water and lemon juice or flavoring.
Continue to stir until mixture gets real thick; make sure the bottom of double boiler has plenty of water in it, but not enough to cause steam to rise while stirring ingredients.
Pour into cooked pie shell.

title: company peas
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender but not brown:
stir in remaining ingredients.
Season with salt & pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat until warm.

title: onion rye bread(yeast bread)
directions: Stir together flours.
Combine 1 1/2 cups flour mixture, brown sugar, yeast and salt.
Heat water, milk, soup mix, butter and caraway seed until very warm (120° to 130°); stir to melt butter. Add warm milk mixture gradually to yeast mixture.
Add 3/4 cup flour mixture; beat 2 minutes.
Add enough remaining flour mixture to make soft dough.
Cover; let rise until double in bulk, about 50 minutes.
Punch down.
Turn into greased 2-quart casserole. Brush top with melted butter.
Cover; let rise until double in bulk, about 30 minutes.
Bake in 350° gas oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from casserole; brush with melted butter.
Cool on rack.
Yield: 1 loaf.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In medium size saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate and butter.
Add milk, coconut, sugar and eggs. Stir until well blended.
Pour mixture into pie crust. Bake 30 minutes until knife inserted in center of filling comes out clean. Serve pie warm or at room temperature. Top with whipped cream or ice cream. Serves 8.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon butter basting sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.

title: pecan cheesecake pie
directions: In another bowl, blend 3 eggs, corn syrup, vanilla and sugar until smooth.
Gently pour mixture over pecans.
Bake on center rack 50 to 60 minutes at 350° until center is set.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix caramels in 1/3 cup Pet milk.
Melt and stir until creamy. Combine cake mix, melted oleo, nuts and balance of Pet milk. Stir.
Place 1/2 dough on the bottom of a cake pan; pat down.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
After cools, cut up in small pieces.
Mix soups and Ro-Tel in saucepan.
Heat in large pan.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish, layer crunched Doritos, then chicken.
Pour soup over Doritos; add cheese on top.
Bake at 375° until cheese melts.

title: bob evans au gratin potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a greased 7 x 11 x 2-inch baking pan, place half of potatoes.
Sprinkle flour, then 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese on top.
Cover with remaining potatoes.
Sprinkle remaining Cheddar cheese, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper over, then pour on the milk.
Pour the butter over top.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes until golden brown.
Delicious!

title: skillet cornbread
directions: Preheat greased 9 or 10-inch heavy ovenproof skillet in a 350° oven. Combine dry ingredients.
Add combined buttermilk, egg and margarine, mixing just until moistened.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Pour into skillet. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Continue baking until cheese is melted.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skin, let cool and peel. Cut in cubes; add salt, pepper and celery salt. Mix eggs, onions and mayonnaise and add to potatoes. Drain pimentos and pickle relish and add to other ingredients.

title: kiss pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks slightly; add sugar, salt and slightly cooled milk.
Cook in double boiler, stirring constantly, until mixture coats spoon.
Add vanilla.
Spoon into 4 serving dishes.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in powdered sugar and melted chocolate. Pour on top of custard.
Chill before serving.

title: company pickle chunks
directions: Cover cucumbers (unpeeled) with boiling water.
Let stand 24 hours; pour off.
Repeat 3 times.
On the 5th day, pour off water and slice the cukes in 1/2-inch slices.
Bring to boil vinegar, sugar, salt and spices.
Pour over slices and let stand 2 days. Bring all to a boil and seal in jars.
An excellent sweet pickle.

title: shrimp cheese cups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
With mixer, beat cheese, 1/4 cup cocktail sauce and seasonings until smooth.
Stir in shrimp. Unroll crescent roll dough; separate into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations together to seal.
Cut rectangle lengthwise together to seal.
