Cut rectangle lengthwise, then crosswise into 4 pieces; press onto bottom and 1/2-inch up sides of muffin cups. Spoon 1 rounded tablespoonful cheese mixture into cups.
Bake 10 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes; remove from pan.
Serve warm; garnish with additional cocktail sauce as desired.
Makes 16.

title: old-fashioned rice pudding
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat well and pour into ovenproof dish eggs, sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Stir in rice, raisins and milk and bake 1 hour.
Turn off oven and let pudding stand in oven just until warm.
Do not stir pudding while baking.
May be served warm or refrigerated and served cold.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until filling is slightly firm.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Make dough and shape into rolls.
Store in refrigerator for at least 1 to 2 hours.
Then cut dough into cookie size and bake 10 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Line bottom of dish with cut up chicken.
Pour melted butter over chicken.
Mix chicken broth with cream of chicken soup.
Pour over chicken.
Mix Bisquick with milk; pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until brown.

title: orange sauce
directions: Mix pudding, Karo and orange juice concentrate.
Gradually stir in evaporated milk.
Then add Cool Whip.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Beat all ingredients together except peanuts.
Fold in peanuts. Slice apples and serve.
Enjoy!

title: aunt madge's potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
When cool, peel and grate.
Melt oleo, add soup, onions, sour cream, cheese and chives.
In large mixing bowl, grate potatoes, and add the sauce; add desired amount of salt and pepper.
Put potato mixture in a large casserole dish. Melt oleo and stir in cracker crumbs, enough crumbs to be coated with oleo.
Top potato mixture with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kraft's cheese ball
directions: Cream together all cheeses.
Add rest of ingredients.
Chill for 1 hour.
Put on cheese platter and sprinkle with crushed pecans.

title: fresh apple salad
directions: In saucepan, stir together pineapple with juice, flour and sugar.
Cook on medium heat until mixture is thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in margarine.
Cool completely.
Stir in diced apples and pour mixture into shallow serving dish.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle chopped pecans on top.

title: spicy white bean dip
directions: Drain the beans but save 1/2 of the liquid.
Puree the beans in a food processor, adding some of the liquid as needed.
Saute the onion and garlic in the oil until golden.
Add in the jalapeno and red pepper. Cook briefly, then add the bean puree and remove from heat.
Stir in the cilantro and add salt to taste.
Use the bean liquid to reach desired consistency.

title: peanut patties
directions: Boil the sugar, milk and corn syrup to the soft ball stage. Add peanuts, food coloring, vanilla and margarine.
Beat until thick.
Drop on waxed paper to cool.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In a large skillet melt margarine over medium heat.
Add mushrooms, bell pepper and onion;
saute 3 minutes.
Add chicken, sherry, bouillon, salt and pepper.
Stir milk and corn starch until smooth;
add to skillet.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat and boil one minute.
Stir in pimientos.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: pasta with creamy vegetables
directions: In large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon olive oil until hot.
Add chicken; saute 5 minutes until cooked through.
Remove and keep warm.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease muffin pans.
Sift together the first 4 ingredients.
Beat egg until frothy.
Add milk and butter. Pour milk mixture into flour mixture and beat with mixer.
Add flour-dusted blueberries to this mixture very quickly.
Pour into muffin tins and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake for 25 minutes or until browned slightly.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine prepared apples and sugar in large mixing bowl; let stand 10 minutes.
Sift flour; add soda, salt and spices; set aside.
Blend oil and egg into apple/sugar mixture.
Add dry ingredients; stirring until blended.
Fold in raisins and walnuts. Spread evenly in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mary's salad dressing
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients thoroughly.

title: fruit salad
directions: Toss lightly and chill.

title: mickey mouse pancakes(made by my dad.)
directions: He gets Mickey Mouse cutter and he puts some strawberries for eyes and nose and peach for the mouth.

title: cole slaw
directions: After grating cabbage, add remaining ingredients.

title: knox blocks squiggles
directions: Mix Knox with cold water; let set until firm.
Mix Jell-O with boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Add Knox mixture; stir well. Refrigerate until set firm.
Cut with cookie cutters or into blocks.

title: delicious pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients; add to dry mixture.
Stir well.
Bake at 350° in loaf pan for 45 minutes. Preheat oven.
Flour and grease pan.
Makes 12 servings at 138 calories per serving.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Bring water to a boil.	Add Kool-Aid and sugar; dissolve. Pour into gallon jug.
Pour in pineapple juice and lemon juice (freeze).
When ready to make punch, thaw for about 5 hours.
Pour into punch bowl and add ginger ale.

title: french cream tarts with fruit
directions: Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Beat until fluffy. Fold in whipped cream or whipped topping and vanilla.
Spoon into pastry shells.
Top with fruit.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry icing
directions: Beat egg white until stiff peaks form.
Add sugar slowly to egg white.
Add frozen strawberries and beat exactly 20 minutes.
No cheating!

title: a sad recipe
directions: So I substituted rice.

title: dirt cups
directions: You will need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) plastic cups.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: banana ripple cake
directions: Grease and flour bottom of 10-inch tube pan.
Melt chocolate chips and water together; cool.
Combine flour, soda, salt and baking powder; set aside.
In another bowl, cream butter; gradually add 1 cup sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks. Combine bananas, sour cream and vanilla.
At low speed, alternately add dry ingredients and banana mixture; blend.
Fold in egg whites (beaten).

title: barbecue time baked beans
directions: Place the beans in a bowl; cover with cold water and soak overnight.
Drain and rinse beans very well under cold water. Place the beans in a large, heavy pot.
Add enough water to cover the beans by 2 inches.
Bring water to a boil, reduce heat to a simmer and cook for 45 minutes, or until beans are tender, but not mushy.
Skim off any foam that rises to the surface.
Drain the beans.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a smooth loaf.
Bake 1 1/4 hours in a 350° oven.
Mix last 3 ingredients for sauce; boil 5 minutes. Baste loaf with sauce every 15 minutes.

title: skillet casserole
directions: Press 3/4 of hamburger into cold skillet.
Layer thin sliced or shredded potatoes, carrots and onions over hamburger and top with remaining hamburger.
Cover with layer of shredded cheese and pour can of mushroom soup over top.
Cover and cook at low heat for approximately 50 minutes.

title: congo bars
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well. Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Spread in pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool in pan.
Cut into squares.

title: goulash(for cold weather days)
directions: Brown ground meat.
Add tomato sauce, Ranch Style beans and rice.
Heat to boiling, then simmer, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with cornbread.
Enjoy!

title: italian creme cake
directions: Cream the sugar, 1 stick oleo and shortening. Then add 5 egg yolks (slowly), flour, baking soda and buttermilk. Then slowly add the nuts, coconut and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Fold in 5 beaten egg whites. Bake in 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cabbage salad
directions: In a large container, arrange all the ingredients in layers. Do not stir.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken in 2 quarts water.
Cool, skin and debone.
Chop celery, onion and pepper; saute in butter.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Combine spaghetti, chicken, sauteed vegetables, pimento, cheese, hot peppers and soup with broth.
Pour into 13 x 9 baking dish and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal-cinnamon crispies
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Grease 2 baking sheets.
In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter.
Add the sugar gradually, then
the molasses
and
beat
until the mixture is light and fluffy.
Beat in
eggs one at a time.
Shut off mixer and add baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and vanilla to the batter. Turn mixer back on and blend.	Add flour and blend.
Last, add the
oats
and nuts and blend.	Drop by rounded teaspoonful on baking
sheet.
Bake for 5 to 9 minutes or until cookies are a medium
brown
and a bit crinkly looking.
It may be necessary to turn the cookie sheet around in the oven so they will brown evenly.
Allow
the
cookies to set on the sheets for about 3 minutes,	then
remove to a wire rack and let cool completely. These
freeze
very well.
Recipe can be halved easily.
Makes one hundred 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: vanilla wafer crumb cake
directions: Cream together sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Beat eggs well.
Mix vanilla wafer crumbs, flour and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients alternately with 1/3 cup sweet milk.
Add to Crisco, sugar and egg mixture.
Add one can of coconut and 1 cup of nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes two 9-inch layers.

title: ropa vieja
directions: Thoroughly brown stew meat.
Add 1/2 to 1 cup water to make beef broth.
Add picante sauce and cook slowly for 2 hours.
Shred with knife and fork.
Serve with black beans and yellow rice.

title: oreo delight
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar in a bowl.
Another bowl mix milk and pudding mix until thick.
Crush Oreos.
Set a little bit aside to use as topping.
Add melted butter to the Oreo mix and stir until moist.
Press into 9 x 13 pan.
I usually buy the disposable aluminum pans at the grocery store.
Fold other ingredients together, including the Cool Whip.
Spread over the crust and sprinkle remaining Oreos on top.

title: buttermilk cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° until golden brown.
This is a soft cookie. When storing them, put waxed paper between layers so they don't stick together.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Stir together, margarine, sugar and milk in heavy 3 qt. saucepan. Bring to boil, stirring constantly over medium heat 5 minutes or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly

to prevent scorching. Remove from heat and gradually stir in chocolate until melted. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well until blended. Pour into a greased 9 x 9 inch pan or a 13 x 9 inch pan. Cool at room temperature. Cut into squares.

title: oven-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large roasting pan, toss ingredients.
Bake 40 minutes, stirring once, until potatoes are tender.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, milk, butter, syrup and salt in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture comes to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook to 238° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and let stand until lukewarm. Add vanilla.
Beat until mixture begins to lose gloss and hold shape.
Stir in almonds and quickly turn into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Let stand until firm before cutting.

title: orange apricot ring
directions: Drain apricots, reserving 1 1/2 cups of syrup.
Puree apricots in blender or put through sieve.
(You'll need 2 cups apricot puree.)
Combine reserved syrup, the gelatin and salt; heat to boiling, stirring to dissolve gelatin.
Remove from heat.
Add apricot puree, orange concentrate and lemon juice; stir to melt concentrate.
Slowly pour 7-Up down side of pan.
To keep bubbles, mix gently with up and down motion.
Pour into 6 1/2-cup ring mold. Chill until firm, 6 hours or overnight.
Unmold and fill center with a combination of mayonnaise and Cool Whip.
Surround mold with various fruits of choice.

title: tish's pecan treats
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla gradually. Fold in pecans.
Drop onto lightly greased cookie sheet by spoonfuls.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: teriyaki barbecue
directions: Crush ginger root and garlic.
Combine with remaining ingredients and blend into a sauce.
Soak meat in sauce overnight. Best meat to use is tenderloin or rib eye, sliced thin.
This will soak about 5 to 6 pounds of meat.

title: fruit punch
directions: Chill all ingredients.
You can make fruit ice rings with fruit and fruit punch and freeze.
Mix all ingredients, keeping orange juice in concentrated form.
Serve in large punch bowl.

title: shepherd's chicken
directions: Lightly coat chicken pieces with cornstarch. Brown on all sides in hot oil in a large skillet with lid over medium heat. Combine wine, soy sauce, ketchup and garlic. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle onion and pepper pieces over chicken. Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Turn pieces over and simmer, covered, 15 minutes longer or until tender. Serve over rice.

title: toffee nut bar
directions: Mix well the shortening and 1/2 cup of brown sugar.
Stir in 1 cup of flour.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole and heat at 350°.

title: vanilla extract
directions: Wash and rinse small olive jars well.
You may use any self-sealing used jars.

title: sour orange pie
directions: Set aside 1/4 cup of sugar for egg whites.
Save egg whites for use in topping.

title: shrimp fondue casserole
directions: Spread bread generously with butter; cut into 1/2-inch cubes. Arrange layer in bottom of buttered casserole, then add layer of shrimp and of cheese, sprinkling each layer with salt and pepper. Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Combine eggs and milk; pour over contents of casserole.
Set in hot water and bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: garden fresh stir-fry
directions: Cut carrots into thirds, then cut into thin sticks.
Bias slice beans into 1-inch lengths.
In a covered saucepan cook carrots and green beans in boiling, salted water for 3 minutes. Add cauliflower; cover and cook 2 minutes more.
Drain well.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: spinach chicken manicotti
directions: Saute small onions, clove of garlic and mushrooms in frying pan with olive oil.
Add cubed chicken, stirring until cooked. Steam 1/2 package fresh spinach, drain and chop.
Add to chicken mixture.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Save 1/2 block of grated cheese for top.
Add all to mixture and stuff this into cooked manicotti noodles.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with stuffed shells.
Add plain sauce on top; sprinkle cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Mix other ingredients.
Combine and mix well; add nuts.
Grease 1 pound coffee cans or anything similar.
Be sure to grease well with Crisco and flour well up to top of can.
Fill about 1/2 full or 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes; test with toothpick.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Spread vegetables in 9 x 13-inch pan.
No need to thaw.
Melt Velveeta and 1 stick margarine.
Pour over vegetables.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix with 1/2 stick margarine.
Spread over top of vegetables and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine butter or margarine, soup and sour cream. Blend well. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Cook in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until slightly browned.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine in double boiler, stirring until thickened.
Remove from heat and add 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Put small amount of custard in bowl (just enough to barely cover bottom).
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas (sliced).
Add 1/3 custard for each layer.
Make 3 layers and end with custard.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Grease bottom of large casserole.
Spread rolls on bottom and bake for 7 or 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Dust with Ranch dressing.
Add vegetables to mixture and press down.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: mother's ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add crushed pineapple and pour into mold or Pyrex dish.
Let set.
Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup hot water and let cool.
Add Philadelphia cream cheese and whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Pour over first layer and let set.
Dissolve cherry jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add pitted and drained Royal Anne cherries and let cool.
Add to second layer and let set.

title: 2-egg cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar at medium speed for 2 minutes. Add vanilla extract and eggs. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture with milk.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 370° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: good oatmeal-chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter and oil.
Add sugars, egg and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Stir in oats and remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients; press down gently.

title: lasagna no. 3
directions: Add all ingredients except noodles and cheese and simmer 40 to 45 minutes.
Layer noodles, sauce and cheese in large, ovenproof baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: icebox rolls
directions: In large mixing bowl, pour 1 cup boiling water over sugar, shortening and salt.
Let cool.
Soak yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water.
When mixture is cool, add yeast to it.
Sift enough flour into it and mix until it looks like biscuit dough.
Cover with clean tea towel and let rise to top of bowl.
Roll out what you want to bake and put the rest in the refrigerator for later use. Cover with a plate.
Cut with biscuit cutter and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.
This is easier to mix with a stiff wooden spoon.

title: western beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer on low, stirring often, until heated.

title: cheesy potato supreme
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; cut into 1/4-inch strips.
Combine 1/4 cup margarine, onion, salt, pepper, sour cream and soup. Gently stir into potatoes.
Add shredded cheese.
Spoon into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and chill.
Soften gelatin in cold water; dissolve over low heat with 3/4 cup of broth.
Add remaining broth and chill until slightly thickened.
Toss macaroni with remaining ingredients.
Chill until set.
Unmold on lettuce lined platter and surround with deviled eggs and cold cuts.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: homemade chili for church groups
directions: Cook hamburger and onions.
Add tomato juice and 1 gallon catsup, then Mexican chili hot beans and chili powder.
Add cornstarch to make thick.
Serves about 100 people, 1/2 of it serves 50 people.

title: hidden valley ranch mashed potatoes
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes from scratch (or instant potatoes according to package), omitting salt.
Stir in Hidden Valley Ranch salad dressing mix (Original Ranch) and add butter.
Serves 4.

title: toasty peach crisp
directions: Mix
flour, cinnamon, brown sugar and oats.
Mix margarine into

flour mixture with a fork until mixture is crumbly. Put peaches in a greased baking pan. Sprinkle crumb mixture on top. Bake at 375° (moderate oven) about 30 minutes until fruit is tender and top is brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: low cholesterol cookies
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar until fluffy; add egg whites and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in flour, soda and salt together.
Blend well.
Add oatmeal, raisins and nuts; again mix well.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheets for 10 minutes or until lightly brown at 375°.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Sift flour.
Combine flour, salt and Crisco in a mixing bowl. Add water; mix.
Shape into 2 equal size balls.
Roll dough. Makes two 9-inch pie crusts.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix and set aside chocolate drink powder and red food coloring.

title: robin's peanut butter pie
directions: Beat heavy cream, until stiff peaks form.
Mix together next 3 ingredients.
Fold into cream.
Fill pie shell.
Garnish with topping and enough crushed peanuts to cover pie.
Refrigerate or freeze until ready to serve.
If frozen, allow to thaw about 30 minutes before serving.

title: potato la creme pie
directions: Add 1/8 teaspoon each:
garlic and onion salt to the flour.

title: oriental rice
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until rice is soft.
Do not overcook.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt; dredge meat in mixture.
Heat skillet, then add 2 tablespoons butter.
When melted, add sirloin strips and brown quickly, flipping meat to brown on all sides.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Cook 3 or 4 minutes, until onion is barely tender.
Remove meat from skillet, add 2 tablespoons butter to pan drippings; when melted, add 3 tablespoons flour and tomato paste.
Slowly pour in cold meat stock; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Return meat mixture to skillet.
Stir in sour cream and heat briefly. Serve with rice.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Brown meatballs thoroughly in butter; pour sauce over meat balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: texas brisket
directions: Put roast in pan and cover with mixture of Coke, chili sauce and onion soup.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours or until tender.
Slice and pour sauce over roast.
I cover the roasting pan with foil with small holes in it.
I usually cook 2 at a time in a slow oven.
It may take 4 hours or so.
It's done when tender.

title: chipmunk bars
directions: Pour boiling water over chopped dates.
Let cool.
In separate bowl, cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture alternately with date mixture; blend well.
Pour batter into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Sprinkle chopped nuts and chocolate chips over batter.
Press lightly into batter.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: stuffed artichoke casserole
directions: Mix together bread crumbs and garlic powder.
In a greased casserole dish, alternate layers of artichoke hearts (cooked, if frozen), bread crumb mixture and cheese.
End with cheese on top. Pour oil and liquid over casserole.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Serve hot.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Drain and wash pickles. Slice crosswise. Pack in jar with garlic buds (cut in half) and put them between layers.

title: frances ward's blueberry pie
directions: Peaches can be substituted for blueberries.

title: prize winning cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Blend in butter and orange extract.
Turn mix into pan and bake 15 minutes at 450°. Refrigerate for at least 12 hours before cutting or serving.

title: zucchini bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice onions and zucchini 1/2 inch thick and place in a large bowl.
Salt thoroughly, cover and allow to rest overnight. Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a rolling boil in large pot.
Add zucchini
and onions to the pickling solution.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Pack pickles into hot sterilized jars.
Fill to 1/2 inch of top with pickling solution. Seal and process in a boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 pints.

title: pat's coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage; chop onion and cucumber.
Add drained pimentos; crumbled Blue cheese.
Add mayonnaise and lemon juice; add horseradish and trim with avocado and cherry tomatoes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat
eggs,
oil and sugar.
Sift together flour, salt, baking soda,
cinnamon
and add to egg mixture.
Stir with big spoon the vanilla,
apples,
pecans
and
coconut
and add to egg-flour mixture.
Stir
together.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes in large tube pan that has been lightly greased (test for doneness with toothpick).

title: california blend soup(microwave)
directions: Heat water to boiling in covered dish in microwave.
Add potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook, uncovered, on high 8-10 minutes; do not drain.
Set aside.
In a 3 qt. dish, melt butter.
Stir in flour and milk.
Cook, uncovered, on high 6-7 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Add cheese.
Heat 1-1 1/2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Stir in corn, reserved vegetables, and california blend veggies.
Cook on high 2-3 minutes or until heated through.
Yield: 2 1/2 qts.

title: butterscotch pudding
directions: Mix flour and brown sugar, adding beaten egg yolks and milk gradually.
Put on to boil and thicken, stirring constantly.
Take off heat.
Add butter and mix well.
Pour into buttered pie dish. To serve as pie, pour into baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites until meringue consistency.
Add 1/4 cup sugar.
Spread over pie and bake in a preheated oven at 340° until meringue is nicely brown.

title: taffy squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and mix.
Add salt, cinnamon and flour; mix well.
Spread dough 1/4 inch thick on cookie sheet.
Beat egg white slightly and spread over dough. Sprinkle nuts on top, pressing slightly.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill; roll into balls and chill again.
Dip in mixture of chocolate chips and paraffin.
Place on wax paper until set.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Sort, wash and soak beans overnight in water.
Next day, drain, rinse and add the onion, chopped celery, green pepper and garlic.
Put in pan and cover with water.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Add the sausage and continue cooking for 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
If necessary, add water (hot) to prevent beans from sticking.
Stir in salt, pepper and Tabasco as mixture simmers.
Add rice in the last 30 minutes. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: chocolate brownie pie
directions: Melt baking chocolate and let stand to cool.
Beat eggs until very light.
Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar to the butter, beating until light and fluffy.
Sift flour and salt together; set aside.
Add the cooled chocolate and the eggs to the creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Alternately add flour mixture and milk (to which the vanilla has been added).
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with ice cream, if desired.

title: snack cake mix
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. With pastry blender, cut in shortening until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Store in airtight container in cool dry place.
Use within 1 month.
Makes about 13 cups.

title: pork chop casserole(microwave recipe)
directions: Place chops in margarine to brown.
Brush with Worcestershire sauce while browning.
Mix onion and celery soup.
Place 1/2 of this mixture in
the bottom of a casserole.
Place chops on top of mixture and cover with remaining soup.
Cook 20 minutes in microwave or until chops are done.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush crackers, add fruits, nuts and coconut.
Melt marshmallows in milk over low heat and add to cracker mixture. Mix well and pack in 2 loaf pans lined with wax paper.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 2 to 3 pound loaf cakes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Add a little garlic powder and grated onion to mayonnaise. Combine ingredients.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer at least 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate zucchini bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: In a mixing bowl beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Wash zucchini.
Peel if tough.
Grind zucchini, onion and peppers.
Put in pan and mix with salt.
Stand overnight in refrigerator.
Rinse in colander and drain.
Place spices, vinegar and sugar with mix.
Blend.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 30 minutes. Put in canning jars while hot to seal.

title: holiday walnuts
directions: Combine sugar, water, honey, and salt in saucepan. Cook on low to medium heat until candy thermometer reads 248 degrees. Remove from heat. Add vanilla and nuts. Stir quickly with wooden spoon. It may take a while, but the mixture will get thick and white, about 4 minutes. Empty onto waxed paper and separate pieces.

title: no bake apricot cheesecake
directions: Puree 10 apricot halves with reserved syrup from can, then heat to boiling.
In a large bowl, mix gelatine and sugar.
Add hot liquid; stir for about 5 minutes, until sugar and gelatine are completely dissolved.
With mixer, beat in cream cheese and vanilla until smooth.
Let stand 10 minutes, then pour into crust.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with remaining apricots and whipped cream.

title: broccoli dish
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix soup and mayonnaise together. Add lemon juice and cheese.
Blend well.
Spoon broccoli into a 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Spoon soup mixture over the top.
Spread bread crumbs on top.
Top with almonds.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix all together.
Roll out on board.
Cut and fry in hot grease (Crisco).

title: no-bake corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo in medium saucepan.
Combine the remaining ingredients, except cheese, in pan and mix well.
Cook over low heat, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
As mixture thickens, lift from bottom with spatula occasionally.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover and cook 15 minutes over low heat without stirring.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: wedding or anniversary punch
directions: In punch bowl, mix all together, except 7-Up.
Add 7-Up just before serving.
Makes 40 cups on ice.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Peel potatoes and dice in small chunks.
Add diced carrots, celery and onions.
Add salt and pepper and cook until tender, about 45 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook additional 15 minutes. Add all other ingredients.
Simmer a few minutes and serve.

title: curried shrimp casserole
directions: Melt oleo; add next 4 ingredients and stir.
Add milk.
Add catsup, sherry and shrimp and mix over heat until thick.
Combine with rice.
Bake in casserole dish at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: peppercorn pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Mix all ingredients with pasta and vegetables in large bowl.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy. Add sugar, butter and vanilla. Beat 1 minute more, then blend in pecans.
Pour into two 9-inch pie shells. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake until filling sets, about 30 minutes.

title: chili chicken bites
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Melt butter or margarine in a 9 inch square pan in oven. Tip pan to coat with butter or margarine. In a large bowl, beat eggs, stir in flour, baking powder, and salt. Add melted butter or margarine. Set pan aside for later. Stir in chilies, cottage cheese and Jack cheese. Mix until blended. Turn batter into coated pan. Bake 15 minutes. Reduce heat to
350°F. Bake 30 - 35 minutes longer or until lightly browned. Cool slightly and cut into small squares. May be frozen.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix and pour in graham cracker crust and chill.
Top with 1 can blueberry, cherry or strawberry pie mix.

title: scripture cake
directions: Follow Solomon's advice for making a good boy in Proverbs 23:14.
Then you will have a good cake.
Place in loaf pan and cook very slowly.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; add the egg and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add applesauce and dry ingredients which have been sifted together and stir until the batter is smooth. Fold in the dates, nuts and raisins.
Turn into a greased bread pan (9 1/2 x 5 1/2 x 3-inches).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: homemade supreme pizza
directions: Prepare pizza crust mix as directed.
Spread on rectangular cookie sheet.
Mix tomato sauce, Italian seasoning, garlic salt and oregano and spread over prepared crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: skyline chili dip
directions: Cook chili according to directions.
Spread cream cheese on the bottom of a glass pie dish.
Top with hot chili.
Add onion and Cheddar cheese.
Serve with chips.
Enjoy.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Melt butter and pour over bananas.
Beat together.
Add sugar and beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Fold in nuts and bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: mini meat loaf casserole
directions: Combine
meat
and seasoning, egg, 1/2 can tomato sauce and 1/2
can French fried onions.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Make into 3 mini loaves.
Place potatoes around loaves. Bake covered
at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
(You can then add extra vegetables
if
you
care
to, like corn, red pepper or broccoli.) Stir potatoes;
add a little salt and pepper.
Pour tomato
sauce on (1/2 can) top of mini loaves.
Bake uncovered 10 minutes; top loaves with other half of French fried onions. Bake for 6 or 7 minutes longer.

title: codfish balls
directions: Shred codfish that has soaked overnight in water.
Boil codfish, then shred.
Mix ingredients and shape into balls.
Deep fry in oil a few at a time.
Drain on paper towel.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from meat and cut into bite-size strips.
Brown in electric skillet.
Add to cans of cream of mushroom soup.
Add tomato paste and water.
Stir together and let simmer for at least 1/2 hour (up to 2 to 3 hours is better).
Just before serving, gently stir in French onion dip.
Serve over rice.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Scrape carrots and cut up.
Combine all ingredients in pan; cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer until carrots are tender.
Uncover and cook over medium heat until liquid evaporates and carrots are glazed.

title: slush drink
directions: Add blender mixture and vodka to Kool-aid mixture.
Put in freezer-safe containers and freeze.
When ready to serve, scoop slush into a glass and add ginger ale or 7-Up.

title: corn custard cups
directions: Puree corn in blender for 1 minute.
Add milk and blend for 1 minute.
Add dry ingredients and blend for 1 minute.
Add eggs and blend for 15 seconds.

title: baked peach pudding
directions: Combine butter and sugar; add dry ingredients to mixture in small amounts, alternating with milk.
Spread over fruit which has been arranged in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs and sugar well.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and slice.
Put the slices in a baking dish. Sprinkle dry soup mix over the top of potatoes.
Melt both sticks of butter or margarine.
Pour over the potatoes and dry soup mix. Bake at 350° for at least 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: vegetable dip (easy)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve with fresh vegetables or chips.

title: cracker jack peanuts
directions: Put in an iron skillet.
Heat slowly and stir constantly until liquid evaporates.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Store in an airtight container.

title: chicken divan
directions: Combine chicken soup, mayonnaise and curry to taste.
Butter a 13 1/2 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer broccoli and chicken and then pour sauce over all.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours until bubbly.
Serve with bread and a salad.

title: ginny's mexican corn bread
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients.
Place half of batter in a greased skillet.
Sprinkle with half of the grated cheese.
Spread a layer of peppers on cheese.
Sprinkle on other half of cheese. Top with rest of the batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice & broccoli
directions: Cook frozen broccoli until tender and drain.
Saute onion and bell pepper in oleo.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in large oblong greased pyrex.
Sprinkle with 1 cup grated American cheese.
Bake 30 min. at 325°.
Serves 14-16.

title: chocolate sundae dessert
directions: Mix chocolate pudding as directed on package and layer over last layer (second layer).
Take last container of frozen topping and use as last layer over the chocolate pudding.
Sprinkle top with nuts or graham cracker crumbs.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Mix in bowl.
Make into balls, walnut size.
Melt almond bark and roll balls into bark.
Sprinkle with nuts (peanuts).

title: pizza favors
directions: Brown together the ground beef and sausage; drain.
Cut and melt into meat the Velveeta cheese.
Add seasonings; mix well. Pile on party rye.
Broil until brown and bubbly.
Makes 70.
May be frozen.

title: diply nacho
directions: Brown the hamburger, sausage and onion together; drain.
Add the seasoning mix with 1 cup of water, then add both cans of soup. Do not dilute.
Stir until well blended.
Great to dip your nachos into.

title: reesie balls
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter and sugar.
Melt butter; add vanilla and combine with the graham cracker mixture. Stir thoroughly and mix with hands.
Form small balls and chill until firm.
In double boiler, melt the wax and chocolate chips. Dip candy balls in the chocolate mixture and let set one hour before serving.

title: summer icebox cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, milk and egg.
Cook to a good boil, 200° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add coconut, nuts and cracker crumbs.
Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with foil.
Line bottom with whole graham cracker squares.
Pour mixture over crackers in pan.
Add layer of crackers on top.
Make Icing and cover top.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour half into large shallow baking dish.
Add yams. Top with remaining syrup.
Bake in 350° oven, basting often, 20 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: peanut butter cupcakes
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs about 1 minute.
Add flour alternating with milk; beat 1 minute.
Add peanut butter and flavoring; mix well.
Pour batter into cupcake pans, filling about 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cut up chicken. Add soups, mayonnaise, salt, pepper and paprika.
Pour over broccoli in baking dish. Top with cheese and bread crumbs. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add beer and beat.
Add egg and beat again.
Pour into oiled loaf pan.
Bake immediately at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: grannie's icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Add to butter mixture.
Add pecans.
Mix thoroughly.
Press and mold into a long, smooth roll, about 2 1/2-inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper, twisting ends.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Place a little apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: eggplant-zucchini casserole
directions: Combine sauce, water, salt, garlic and basil.
Layer 1/2 of vegetables, spaghetti cheese and tomato mixture in greased 3-quart casserole (in order listed).
Repeat process.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hearty white and black bean soup
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven, combine all ingredients, except sour cream. Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low. Cover and cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve with sour cream. Makes 9 1/2 cups or 8 servings.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Have sausage and cheese at room temperature.
Grate cheese and mix thoroughly with sausage.
Add Bisquick and mix thoroughly. Form into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Mix and place in pie plate.
Save 1 tablespoon for top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put rice in buttered dish.
Add sugar, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Mix.
Add milk and mix.
Add heavy cream and mix.
Dot top with 2 tablespoons of butter.
Bake at 300° (slow oven) for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar together.
Add egg yolks. Mix flour and soda together, also coconut and nuts together.
Add all other ingredients together.
Fold in egg whites last.
Bake at 350° until done.
Top with Cream Cheese Icing.
This cake can be baked in layers or a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine Bisquick and 3/4 cup artificial sweetener.
Make a well in center of mixture and add sour cream and egg all at once.
Beat with a fork until well combined. Gently fold in blueberries.
Put 1/4 cup of batter in each muffin cup.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Mix butters together with eggs and sugars.
Roll into balls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or less.
Bake to rise up good.
Take out of oven and put a Hershey's Kiss on top of each cookie and lightly press into cookie, not all the way down.
Bake 2 to 5 minutes more until Kiss is soft and take out and cool.

title: velveeta con queso dip
directions: Cut cheese into small squares. Microwave Velveeta cheese and tomatoes with green chilies in a 1 1/2-quart microwavable bowl on High for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Stir after 3 minutes. Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine the 2 kinds of corn.
Stir in sour cream.
Add slightly beaten eggs and melted margarine.
Stir in muffin mix. Do not overbeat.
Pour into ungreased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top with cheese.
Put back in oven until cheese melts.
Cool 10 minutes.
Great to serve as a side dish with ham at Easter!

title: maple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in bottom of 8-inch round cake pan.
Mix in maple sugar.
Arrange pineapple chunks to cover bottom of pan.
Mix beaten egg yolks with sugar; add milk and extract, then dry ingredients, sifted together.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour batter over pineapple.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° about 45 minutes.
Invert and serve out in wedges, garnished with whipped cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Using an electric mixer, beat well butter, Crisco and sugar. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each yolk.
Sift together flour and soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk, then add vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Last, fold in egg whites, beaten stiff. Bake in three 8-inch pans at 350° for 35 minutes or until done. Cool on wire rack.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo and cream cheese.
Add to corn and Ro-Tel.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese lime pie
directions: Make 3 1/2 hours before serving.
In large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in 1/2 cup milk.
Reduce speed to low.
Add pudding mix, undiluted limeade concentrate and remaining 1 cup milk; beat just until blended.
Fold in 2 cups whipped topping; spoon into pie crust. Refrigerate pie until cream cheese filling is firm enough to slice, at least 3 hours.
To serve, spoon remaining whipped topping into decorating bag with star tube.
Decorate pie.
Makes 10 servings.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat eggs; stir in and beat milk, flour, baking powder and salt, then beat in oil.
Add corn to fritter batter.
Drop by spoonful into hot fat.

title: chili(reba style)
directions: Brown meat in 2 tablespoons oleo, add chopped onion and bell pepper in slow cooker or large stew pot.
Have 16 ounce can of tomatoes, 15 ounce can of tomato sauce plus one can of water, add meat, onion and bell pepper mix to stew pot.
Add the 2 packs of chili seasonings, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 to 2 hours.

title: spaghetti with chicken breast
directions: Heat oil in saucepan.
Add onions and saute until golden.
Add chicken and saute until golden.
Stir in corn, chicken broth, salt and paprika.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water until just tender, following package directions.
Drain.
Place pasta in heated serving dish.
Spoon chicken mixture on top and toss well.
Sprinkle with chives and serve.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix boiling water and oatmeal together. Let stand 20 minutes. In separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients together. Add oatmeal and water mixture. Bake at 350° until done.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Roll up again and let stand until set.

title: dirt salad
directions: Drain fruit, mix together all 3 cans.
Add whipped topping and pistachio pudding mix and you may add nuts, marshmallows or coconut (if desired).

title: potato soup
directions: Spray a 3-quart kettle with no-stick spray.
Saute garlic, onion and celery in oil.
Add turkey or ham, raw potatoes and water.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover kettle and simmer 20 minutes.
Add salt, black pepper and skim milk.
Heat to almost boiling.
Add more salt and pepper, if desired.
Serve.

title: batter pudding
directions: Sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt several times.
Add melted butter to sugar and stir in egg and milk.
Put berries in pie plate and dredge with flour mixture.
Sift flour into liquid mixture; mix.
Fold in berries.
Pour into buttered steamer; cover and steam for 1 hour.
Serve warm with foamy pudding sauce.

title: two layer cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar slowly.
Add well beaten eggs, beating well.
Add vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake in 2 layer cake pans about 25 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain; cool and place in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and chill.

title: sweet 'n sour pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; add oil and toss.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Keeps one to two weeks.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli florets, onions and raisins in large bowl. Blend mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar to make the dressing.
Toss all ingredients with dressing just before serving and top with bacon bits.

title: hot and sweet mustard
directions: Mix vinegar and mustard together.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Add eggs and sugar.
Bring all of this to slow boil in pan and let cook until the mixture coats the back of a spoon (about 10 minutes).
Cool and refrigerate.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan; bake 8 minutes at 400°; cool completely.
Beat Ricotta and sweetener together.
Fold in whipped topping. Carefully spread over pretzel layer.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add strawberries and chill until thickened.
Spoon over cheese layer; let chill overnight or until completely thickened. Makes 8 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together before adding beans.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: sticky buns
directions: Prepare yeast roll mix as directed on package.
While dough is rising, combine 3/4 cup brown sugar, 1/2 cup butter and water; mix until blended.
Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan; sprinkle pecans over syrup.

title: bow tie pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to box; drain.
Cook vegetables according to package.
Combine pasta and vegetables with remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Cover and chill until ready to serve. Makes about 8 servings.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add each ingredient as listed, spreading out over pan.
Bake in oven at 350° until chips ar slightly melted.

title: peppermint schnapps
directions: Boil sugar and water until clear.
Add 90 proof alcohol and peppermint extract.
Use food coloring, if desired.

title: english toffee
directions: Place butter and water in electric frypan.
Set at 400°.
Melt butter with water, then add sugar and stir.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes (about 270° or 280° on candy thermometer), stirring constantly. When cooked, pour out on cookie sheet.
Immediately place Hershey bars on top to cover.
When soft, swirl with spatula.
Sprinkle ground walnuts on top.
Use back of spoon to press nuts into chocolate.
Cool and break into pieces.
Christmas must; makes great gifts.

title: cheesy-broccoli tuna bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles for 20 minutes.
Blend soup and milk into smooth sauce.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Mix all the ingredients in 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix cake according to cake mix directions with mixer.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven 40 to 45 minutes.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: I like pork ribs best but this works good on beef, too.
Put ribs in 1 or 2 big pots.
Cover with water.
Add a spoonful of salt and a little pepper to each pot.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cover with lid and cook for about an hour.
Remove ribs and put in a baking pan.
I like a cast-iron Dutch oven.
Add a layer of ribs and cover with your favorite barbecue sauce.
Add more ribs and more sauce until all used.
Cook in oven at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and cook another 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream the sugar and butter real good. Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add flour and soda, alternating with sour cream.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in greased and floured tube pan or angel food pan.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease small shallow baking pan. Blend artichokes in blender of food processor or chop finely. Combine mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese in medium bowl.
Add to chopped or blended artichokes and blend again.
Pour into greased dish, spreading evenly in dish.
Bake until top is browned, about 20 minutes.

title: angels on horseback
directions: Drain oysters.
Lay each oyster on half a slice of bacon. Sprinkle with seasonings and chopped parsley.
Roll bacon around oyster and fasten with toothpick.
Place oysters on a rack in shallow pan and bake in hot oven until bacon is crisp.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs, flour, syrup and vanilla.
Mix well.
Put in large pan or 2 (8-inch) square greased pans.
Spread chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: carrot cake with lemon glaze
directions: In medium bowl, toss carrots with pecans; set aside.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
Beat eggs with electric mixer.
Beat in oil and vanilla. Gradually beat in flour mixture, then carrot mixture.
Turn into well-greased pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.
Cool 15 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: oriental salad
directions: Crush noodles and mix with all other ingredients.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Spray Bundt cake pan with Pam.
Put in frozen rolls.
Mix dry ingredients and nuts; sprinkle over rolls.
Pour melted butter over all.
Let set overnight or 8 hours.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: In a 2-quart pan, combine sugar, syrup and water plus salt. Cook and stir until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to a boil; cook to hard ball stage.
Immediately beat egg whites stiff.
Pour in hot syrup, a very small amount at a time, slowly, at highest speed of electric mixer.
Keep bowl moving around until soft peaks form, then add nuts.

title: old fashion 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, milk and vanilla.
Add flour; mix well.
Place batter in pan and bake at 350° until center springs back when touched.
Use any size or shaped pan and adjust baking time accordingly.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Cook hamburger, seasoning with salt and pepper to taste; drain grease.
In crock-pot, combine hamburger, both cheeses and Tabasco (to taste).
Cover and let melt, stirring occasionally and adding milk as needed.
Serve with chips.

title: chicken with sherry
directions: Place chicken in a shallow baking pan, which is large enough to that the pieces don't touch each other.
Pour melted butter over chicken pieces.
Mix the soup, sour cream and sherry.
Pour these ingredients over the chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Enjoy!

title: ham casserole
directions: Lightly brown ham and onion in butter.
Stir in soup, milk 3/4 cup cheese into ham mixture until cheese melts.
Blend with macaroni and pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until light brown and bubbly.

title: oven cheese chowder(serves 8. preparation:  10.  cook:  1:10.  total:  1:20.)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, in a 3-quart baking dish. Cover and bake at 400° for one hour, stirring halfway through. Stir in cheese. Bake an additional 10 minutes. Nutrition (per serving):
256 calories.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into baking dish.
Top with corn flakes, potato chips or French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(If potatoes are not completely thawed, allow additional baking time.)

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift flour, soda and cinnamon together.
Add to cream mixture alternately with milk.
Add to nuts and fruit mixture.
Bake at 250° or 300° for 20 minutes.

title: andrea's favorite blueberry pancakes
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until blended.
Add blueberries.
Pour onto hot griddle.
Cook until edges are dry. Turn, cook until golden.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Grease a 3-quart casserole dish. Combine corn and beaten eggs; set aside.
Mix together dry ingredients: sugar, cornstarch, salt, and dried onion; add to corn mixture.
Stir in milk and melted butter.
Pour into the greased casserole.
Bake 60 minutes, stirring once.

title: onion swiss steak
directions: Pound steak with flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown in oil; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to steak.
Cover and simmer over low heat 2 hours or until meat is tender, stirring often.
Add water as necessary.

title: chocolate nut bar
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine crumbs and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 8 minutes; reduce oven temperature to 350°.
In small saucepan, melt 1 cup chocolate chips with Eagle Brand and vanilla.
Spread chocolate mixture over prepared crust.
Top
with remaining 1 cup chocolate chips, then nuts.
Press down firmly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool; chill, if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: broccoli topped tuna bake
directions: Prepare macaroni or noodles; drain.
Reserve 1/2 cup Cheez Whiz.
In large bowl combine cream of mushroom soup, milk and remaining Cheez Whiz.
Stir in macaroni, tuna fish and pepper. Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Stir top with broccoli and pour in remaining Cheez Whiz. Bake 5 minutes longer or until hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: raw sweet potato cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs together.
Add oil.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Add sweet potatoes and nuts.
Bake in a sheet pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or cook in a tube pan at 300 degrees for approximately 1 hour.

title: spiced cranberry ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin, salt, cinnamon and cloves in boiling water. Add cranberry sauce and orange rind.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in oranges and apple.
Pour into 6 cup mold.
Garnish as desired. Makes 12 servings.

title: oven stew
directions: Mix well.
Place in oven at 350°.
Do not remove cover for 2 hours; then check and bake longer if necessary.

title: woman's day no-bake cheese cake
directions: Lightly grease a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Mix cracker crumbs and butter until blended.
Press over bottom about 3/4-inch up sides of pan.
Place in freezer while making filling.
Sprinkle gelatin over water in a small saucepan.
Let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat 2 to 3 minutes until completely dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Beat cream cheese and sugar in a large bowl with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Beat in sour cream.
With mixer on low speed, beat in orange juice and gelatin.
Beat in peel.
Pour into chilled crust.
Cover pan and refrigerate at least 4 hours or until firm.
A few hours before serving, run a thin knife around edge of cheesecake to loosen from pan.
Remove pan sides.
Top cake with sliced oranges or cut and place sliced oranges on each piece.

title: home-baked beans
directions: Rinse beans.
Cover with water overnight.
In the morning, cook slowly until skins burst.
Drain and save liquid.
Put into roaster and add all ingredients.
Cover and bake in slow bake at 250° to 300° until beans are tender.

title: cheer wine ice cream
directions: Fill ice cream can up to about 1 inch from top.
Freeze per freezer instructions.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a buttered baking dish.
Top with more crumbled crackers and dabs of butter.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350 degree oven until brown.

title: star rice
directions: Melt butter
in heavy skillet;	stir in rice and brown. Add onions
and cook slightly.	Add to other ingredients. Cook in casserole
at
for
minutes
(dish freezes well). Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican hot cocoa
directions: In saucepan, combine milk, sugar, chocolate, cinnamon and salt.
Heat, stirring, until chocolate melts and milk is very hot. Slowly stir 1 cup of milk into eggs and return to saucepan.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat with mixer until frothy.
Pour into mugs and serve.
Serves 6.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, crackers, little bit of ketchup, onions, brown sugar and eggs.
Then the topping:
1 cup ketchup, brown sugar and nutmeg.
Bake.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Alternate flour and milk.
Add salt and baking powder. Stir in flavorings.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry-lemonade punch
directions: Chill ginger ale or 7-Up.
Be sure it is well chilled.
In punch bowl, combine lemonade, orange juice, strawberries and 3 cups water.
Refrigerate to stay cold.
Just before serving, pour 7-Up or ginger ale into punch bowl.
Stir well.
Garnish with lemon, lime and orange slices.
You can mold ice with strawberries in ring mold; use extra pink lemonade and place in punch bowl.

title: cucumber horseradish mold
directions: Pour boiling water over lime gelatin and stir until dissolved. Soften plain gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve in boiling liquid; cool.
Add salt, juice and horseradish.
Chill until partially thickened.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Turn into large mold or 6 small molds and chill until firm.

title: no bake fruitcake
directions: Chop cherries and raisins; set aside.
Melt butter and marshmallows in double boiler or heavy nonstick pan.
Add cracker crumbs, nuts, cherries and raisins.
Mix well.
Pack in a buttered glass casserole dish.
Let cool.

title: cherry oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine shortening, butter and sugars; beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add cherries, coconut, oats and sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Chill one hour.
Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in 375° (moderate) oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. After one minute, remove cookies to racks and cool.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, Crisco and salt.
Save out 1 cup of mixture. To the remaining crumbs, add warm water, molasses and soda.
Mix together into greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: roquefort cheese dip
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Beat until creamy, using buttermilk to desired consistency.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Pare and cut carrots very thin.
Put with margarine in frying pan.
Cover, but stir them often.
When getting soft, add the brown sugar or maple syrup.
Watch closely.
Cook until tender.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until mixture is thoroughly blended and foamy. Add remaining ingredients and blend. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Serve with unsweetened whipped cream if desired.

title: southern pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour and vanilla.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: pickled dill okra
directions: Bring vinegar to boil with water and salt.
Leave 1/4-inch stem on okra.
Pack in jars with dill, garlic, red pepper and alum.
Add hot vinegar mixture.
Leave 2 weeks before serving.

title: creamy reception punch
directions: Spoon out sherbet into punch bowl.
Add juices; stir.
Slowly add soda; stir gently.
Makes 36 (4-ounce) servings.

title: beef tips and gravy
directions: Mix all ingredients togther and place in a 1 1/2 qt. casserole, cover and bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in pan.
Add water and cook, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Stir in gelatin (while hot). Chill until partly set.
Place strawberries in pie shell and cover with gelatin mixture.
Chill at least 3 to 4 hours.

title: cherry-orange salad
directions: Combine orange juice and water in saucepan.
Stir well and bring to a boil.
Combine cherry and orange jello in a mixing bowl.
Add hot orange juice mixture, stirring until gelatin dissolves.
Set aside to cool while preparing the other ingredients.
Stir in carrots, fruit and nuts.
Chill until mixture is consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold remaining ingredients into gelatin.
Chill until firm.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour, salt and cocoa together. Add to mixture. Mix well and add vanilla. Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven. Spread the marshmallow cream over top of cake when removed from oven. Set aside to cool.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Blend soup and water in a 2-cup measuring cup.
Microwave 3 minutes on Medium.
Stir after 1 1/2 minutes.

title: deer chili
directions: In large pot, brown meat.
Then add onion and garlic, then let cook 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.

title: potato wraps
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash potatoes and cut into quarters. Sprinkle each with a mixture of seasoned salt, seasoned pepper and bay leaves.
Wrap 1 bacon piece around each potato piece. Sprinkle with any remaining seasonings.
Place in baking dish and bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes or until bacon is crisp and potatoes are cooked through.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve, if desired, with sour cream and chives.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until just tender and cool.
Boil eggs 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool in cold water and peel at once.
Dice cooled potatoes and eggs.
Add chopped onion and celery.
Add salad dressing to cover and mix.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, nutmeg and vanilla; mix well. Add milk and stir well. Pour into large unbaked pie shell and sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes or until knife stuck in center comes out clean.

title: yankee banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and egg yolks and gradually add milk. Add margarine and vanilla. Cook on medium heat until thickened. In a big bowl, crumble graham crackers until 1 1/2-inches thick. Slice a layer of bananas on top. Pour 1/2 of pudding over bananas. Add 1 more layer of crackers, bananas and pudding.

title: garden dip
directions: Heat cheese and milk on low power until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Serve with veggies and corn chips.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, melt butter in double boiler.
Stir in flour until smooth, then milk.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Add onion, orange rind, celery salt, parsley, green pepper, salt and red pepper.
Stir egg mixture into rest of sauce.
Flake crab meat and fold into sauce.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Toss bread crumbs with cheese, then sprinkle around top edge of casserole.
Bake 10 minutes.
Arrange tomato slices down center of casserole.
Bake few minutes longer at 350° until crumbs are golden brown.

title: black-eyed pea stew
directions: Brown meat, onions and pepper in 3-quart pot. Add peas and tomatoes. Add seasoning salt and pepper to taste. Simmer 45 minutes.

title: ranch dip
directions: Blend well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Put out 30 minutes before serving to room temperature.
Serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Pour over meatballs and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Put in deep dish pie pan.
Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon and cut butter into mixture until crumbly.
Put onto apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: barbecued lima beans
directions: Cut bacon in half. Fry until crisp and place to drain.
Pour off fat until 2 tablespoons left.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook slowly until brown.
Can use a little bit of garlic powder.

title: mini morsel pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch fluted tube pan or 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Blend in vanilla.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in mini morsels.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 70 to 80 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan.

title: double chocolate bars
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Stir together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Stir into egg mixture.
Spread in bottom of greased 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over top. Bake 3 minutes longer.
Cool.

title: german cookies
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar in mixing bowl.
Add beaten egg to sugar mixture.
Add cinnamon to mixture until completely blended.
Add flour gradually.
Dough will become very hard to mix.
Final blending may need to be done by hand.
Chill dough. Once chilled, roll out to less than 1/4-inch and cut into desired shapes.
Bake for 6 to 10 minutes at 350° on ungreased pan.
Allow cookies to cool and store in plastic container.

title: chocolate pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Add water and vanilla. Roll out.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: crock-pot pork sauce for pasta
directions: Cut pork steaks into strips about 1/2-inch thick and 2-inches long.
In large skillet or crock-pot (if it has a browning unit), brown meat on all sides in oil.
Combine all remaining ingredients in a bowl; mix well and pour over meat in slow cooker.
Cover pot; turn on low and cook for 6 to 8 hours or until meat is tender. Serve with pasta.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a spoon. Do not use a mixer because it will tear up the cherries. Put in a greased and floured 13 x 9 inch baking pan. Bake about 40 minutes at 350°. Make icing and pour over the still warm cake.

title: ginger pickles(mildred gregory)
directions: Soak for 2 weeks in salt water strong enough to float an egg. Drain, wash, let stand in fresh water 24 hours.
Drain.
Let stand in alum water (2 tablespoons) for 24 hours.
Drain.
Pack in strong ginger water (1 tablespoon) for 1 hour.
Drain.
Cut into strips before going in alum water.
Bring vinegar, sugar, pickling spice, and water to boil for 7 minutes and pour over pickles.
Drain and bring to a boil for 7 times morning and evening.

title: popcorn cake
directions: In double boiler, melt butter and stir in marshmallows.
Stir until melted and well blended.
Add popcorn and mix well in large bowl. Press mixture into greased tube pan.
Allow to set overnight.

title: judy's jogging in a jug
directions: Drink 2 to 4 ounces per day.

title: crumb apple pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Sprinkle over apples sliced 1/4-inch thick.
Toss.
Heap in pastry-lined 9-inch pie pan. Sprinkle filling with the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: icebox vegetable salad
directions: Mix and boil slightly the last four ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate.
Will keep for a week.
Serve with a slotted spoon.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix together in buttered dish.
Pepper to taste.
No salt. Use oblong pan.
Use raw chicken breast or legs preference.
Dip chicken into 2 sticks melted butter or margarine.
Lay on top of rice.
Pour remaining butter over chicken and rice.
Bake uncovered at 300° to 325° until chicken is brown.
Serve with cranberry jelly sauce.

title: hash brown hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a shallow pan.
(Cake pan works well; do not use a casserole dish.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Beat eggs and milk slightly.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Fold in cheese and sausage.
Place bread slices in greased casserole.
Pour mixture over bread.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cook uncovered.

title: creamy lemon frosting
directions: Note:
For variation, omit lemon peel and extract and use 2 teaspoons vanilla.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown onion and garlic in cooking oil.
Add ground chuck and brown.
Add tomatoes, water and wine, tomato paste and spices. Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
Put shrimp soup and cream cheese in pan over low heat to melt.
Add gelatin to water and add to soup mixture.
Add onion, celery, mayo and shrimp; pour into mold and chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Freeze. Prepare ahead of time; keeps well.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: clara's kisses(forgotten cookies)
directions: Turn oven to 350°. Beat egg whites with salt. Add sugar gradually.
Beat until very stiff.
Fold in chips and mix well. Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet. These stay in the shape you put them.
By this time, the oven should be heated to 350°.
Put kisses in the oven. Turn the oven off and leave overnight.

title: pumpkin tea loaf
directions: Blend together sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Beat.
Stir in pumpkin until well mixed.
Combine dry ingredients and stir into pumpkin mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat, salt and pepper and onion.
Drain.
Pour enchilada sauce in bowl.
Dip (one at a time) tortillas in sauce.
Line bottom of pan with tortillas.
Pour soup and milk in bowl.
Mix well, then layer on top of tortillas.
Repeat soup, cheese and sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rosalynn carter's strawberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-inch tube pan or 10-inch Bundt pan.
Combine cake mix, strawberry gelatin, vegetable oil, nuts, eggs, flour and strawberries in a large bowl.
Beat.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until cake is done. Cool for 10 minutes on a rack, turn out of pan and cool completely.
Serve plain or with sweetened whipped cream.

title: black bean soup
directions: Saute scallions and garlic in oil.
Add chicken broth and black beans and cilantro.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Puree.
Serve with sour cream and lime juice.
Serves approximately 4.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Stir well.
Makes 2 cups.
(Rather than mince, throw in food processor.)

title: banana bonbons
directions: Heat 1/2 cup water with dates.
When hot, put into blender and blend while slowly adding the balance of the water, 1/2 cup. Blend until smooth, add carob powder.

title: how to make play clay
directions: Stir together baking soda and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add water and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches consistency of moist mashed potatoes (approximately 10 to 15 minutes).
If clay is cooked too long, finished crafts may crack.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: In large bowl, toss together broccoli, cheese, onion, basil, salt and pepper.
Spoon into pastry shell.
In small bowl, stir together cornstarch and milk until smooth.
Stir in eggs until well blended.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: tarin's tostada dip
directions: Mix together and serve with Mexican chips.

title: roll in sugar yeast cookies
directions: Soften the yeast in the warm water. Cream the butter in a large bowl.
Blend in the flour, yeast mixture and vanilla. Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch balls. Roll in granulated sugar. Place on greased cookie sheet. Let rise 15 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Combine ingredients.
Shape into patties.
Fry in hot oil over medium heat until golden brown on each side.
Drain on paper towels and serve immediately.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together the sugar, oil, eggs, orange juice and vanilla. Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to first mixture.
Stir in apples, pecans and coconut.
Pour mixture in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake leaves sides of pan.

title: a gallon of muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Next, combine buttermilk, sugar, eggs and baking soda, and mix with cereal mixture.
Add whole wheat flour, white flour and salt to mixture.
Pour batter into closed containers (quart fruit jars may be used) and store in refrigerator, not freezer.
Batter will keep 3 to 4 months.
To cook, fill greased muffin cups about 3/4 full and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield: 130 small muffins.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put milk, brown sugar, white sugar and oleo in pan.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Put a teaspoon of mixture in cold water.
If it stays together by forming into a ball, it is ready.
Remove from heat.

title: 7 layer taco dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning. Layer in order proceeding.
Serve with chips (nachos).

title: swedish potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets.

Butter 2-quart casserole dish. Cube cooked potatoes into dish. Melt Velveeta cheese in cream (either in double boiler or microwave) to make a smooth sauce. Add remaining ingredients to potatoes with exception of bacon.
Pour cheese sauce over potatoes and top with crumbled bacon. Bake at 350° or 375° for 20 minutes or until brown on top.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in large container in order given.
Drop by tablespoon and flatten on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: spice cake
directions: Either add spices and soda to the flour or in order given in recipe.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Frost with Caramel Icing.

title: crunch apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in deep dish pie shell.
Bake on bottom rack of oven on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until apples are soft and crust is golden brown.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef with the garlic; add parsley, basil, salt, stewed tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Simmer.
Cook 7 to 8 lasagna noodles and rinse with cold water.
Mix the cottage cheese, eggs, salt, pepper, parsley flakes, Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese. Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan:
1/2 noodles, 1/2 cheese mixture and 1/2 meat mixture.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pecan bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil.
Mix dry ingredients together. Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in the partially thawed, undrained berries and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes in a greased loaf pan.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove; cool on a wire rack.
Wrap and store in the refrigerator.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: Combine sugar and pineapple.
Let come to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Add softened cream cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Cool.
Fold in apples, nuts, celery and whipped topping.

title: dump cake
directions: In a buttered 8 x 12-inch pan, place all ingredients and mix. Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour.
In pan, mix oleo, water and cocoa.
Bring to boil.
Pour over flour mixture and mix well.
Add milk, mixed with soda, cinnamon, beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°.
Frost while hot.

title: potato salad(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Boil potatoes 30 minutes or until done.
Drain.
Cool.
Peel and dice.
Boil eggs 15 minutes.
Cool.
Shell and dice.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix together chicken, soup, mushrooms, sour cream and lemon juice.
Spread in baking dish.
Top with crackers and pour butter on top.
Sprinkle with poppy seed and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: lime ring salad
directions: Stir gelatin into 1 cup boiling water until dissolved.
Add food color.
In 2-quart saucepan over low heat, stir marshmallows with remaining 1 cup boiling water until melted.
Add to gelatin. Using mixer at medium speed, gradually beat undrained pineapple into cream cheese until blended.
Stir in gelatin mixture.
Fold in whipped cream and pecans.
Spoon into 6 1/2 ring mold.
Cover; chill until set.
Unmold onto serving plate.
If desired, dip seedless red grapes in sugar; shake off excess.
Pile into center of ring.
Makes 12 servings.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and place in greased casserole.
Pour over top enough tomato juice to just moisten.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, adding more tomato juice if necessary to keep moist.

title: cheese balls
directions: Grate cheese; mix in cream cheese, then mix in all other ingredients. Make sure it is soft enough to work with hands. Divide in half and put on wax paper.
Roll in about 8-inch roll. Chop pecans real fine.
Roll ball over pecans until completely covered.
Put in refrigerator and chill.

title: lexi's sweet potato muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins.
Puree sweet potatoes.
Cream the butter and sugar.
