Beat eggs into pureed sweet potatoes and blend into butter and sugar mixture.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add dry ingredients alternately by hand with milk and nuts.
Do not overmix.
Spoon into tins, filling each tin completely full. Sprinkle a little sugar and cinnamon on top of each muffin.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: cheesy corn chowder
directions: *Can substitute 2 cans cream-style chicken for broth and diced chicken.
Add water to make 3 cups.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix and store in covered containers.
Use 4 to 5 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: rotel potatoes
directions: Cook onion and pepper in butter.
Add remaining ingredients. Blend together.
Cook potatoes until almost done.
Then pour onion mixture over potatoes and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: milwaukee pork chops
directions: Brown chops in frying pan or electric skillet.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer slowly until tender, at least one hour.
The longer they simmer, then thicker the sauce gets and the better they taste.

title: zucchini souffle
directions: In a large bowl mix all ingredients well.
Place in oiled Pyrex dish
(9 x 13-inch).
Sprinkle top with paprika and Romano or Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kiwi fruit and ginger sparkle
directions: Blend the cut up kiwi, peach and ice in a blender until liquefied, at least one minute.
Divide into 2 tall glasses, fill with ginger ale.
Garnish with slices of kiwi fruit.

title: venison stew
directions: Heat oil in large pot.
Brown meat.
Add onions, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, bay leaf, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Continue to cook 30 to 45 minutes.
Mix flour and water together.
Stir into stew.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add Kitchen Bouquet if desired.
Remove bay leaf.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs for 1 minute.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Fold in apples and nuts. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: the all-american dessert
directions: Dissolve each flavor of gelatin completely in 2 cups boiling water in separate bowls. Stir 1 cup cold water into each.
Pour into separate 13 x 9-inch pans. Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm. Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Layer gelatin cubes, whipped topping, cake and strawberries in 3-quart serving bowl.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping and Jell-O star jigglers. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Serves 12 to 16.

title: low-fat sugar-free lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix pudding with 2 1/2 cups skim milk; fold in Cool Whip Light. Pour in 2 graham cracker crusts. Let set 2 hours. Serves 8.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together and stir into creamed mixture. Stir in the vanilla and milk.
Add the black walnuts, then eggs and mix well.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 375° until cake is done.

title: marion's cold poached salmon
directions: Choose any size piece of salmon and clean.
Squeeze over it some lemon juice and ground pepper.
Wrap the fish in foil.
Boil up some water and place the fish into the water when boiling. Cover and boil for exactly 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and leave undisturbed in a cool place.
When the water is completely cool, the fish is cooked.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cover raisins with hot water; boil 1 minute and cool.
Drain. Cream sugars and shortening; beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients with sour milk.
Stir in oatmeal, then chopped nuts, chocolate chips and raisins.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 325° about 10 minutes.

title: easy butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, like piecrust, until soft.
Flatten small balls of dough on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix the eggs, oil, vanilla, sugars and the flour, soda and salt, then cereal, oats and coconut and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 14 minutes.
Makes a dishpan full.

title: indiana-style corn dogs
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients together.
Pour mixture into tall glass.
Skewer hot dogs with wooden skewers; dip in mixture. Deep-fry at 375° until golden brown, about 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towel and enjoy.

title: two egg cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add shortening, vanilla and 1/2 of the milk.
Beat two minutes.
Add rest of milk and eggs.
Beat two minutes.
Pour into greased and floured pans and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes two (9-inch) layers or one 13 x 9-inch.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt. Combine egg, water and vinegar. Pour liquid in all at one time. Blend with spoon just until flour is all moistened. Can be refrigerated up to 2 weeks. Makes 2 double crusts.

title: beans with dumplings
directions: Combine flour, corn meal and baking powder; set aside. Combine egg, milk and cooking oil; set aside.
Cook onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon hot oil in 10-inch skillet until tender, but not brown.
Stir in beans, chili and salsa; bring to boil. Meanwhile add milk mixture to the corn meal mixture.
Stir just enough to combine.
Drop the corn meal mixture in 8 mounds on top of bean mixture.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes, covered. Stick toothpick in dumplings to see if done.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and let stand 2 to 3 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Serves 4.

title: stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onion thoroughly; drain.
Add soup, milk and flour.
Add a little water, if needed.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Add vinegar 5 minutes before serving over noodles or potatoes.

title: crab dip
directions: Choose only soft avocados if you can (hint:
to soften, place in brown paper bag with flour for a few days); peel and remove the seed.
Crush the avocado until as smooth as possible and add 1/2 to 1 cup finely chopped red tomatoes and 1/2 to 1 cup picante sauce. Mix well and serve on beds of finely shredded lettuce.
Great with chips, Tostitos, Doritos, crackers or with any Mexican entre.

title: fudge
directions: Heat sugar, condense and butter. While cooking, watch for burning; boil this mixture for 5 minutes, remove from heat. Mix Hershey bars, chocolate chips, marshmallow cream and walnuts in a large bowl. Pour heated mixture over ingredients in bowl, stir rapidly in bowl to blend until creamy. Pour into buttered shallow pan.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and cube chicken; put in bottom of greased pan (13 x 9-inches).
Top with cooked broccoli.
Mix next five ingredients and pour over chicken and broccoli.
Toss stuffing mix in melted margarine and sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add thawed, mashed raspberries, then add applesauce.
Chill 2 hours.

title: mouse snack
directions: Completely cover the piece of banana with wafer crumbs.
Push the 2 almond slices into top of banana for the mouse's ears.
Use the peanut butter to "glue" on raisin eyes and a chocolate chip for the nose.
Stick pretzel sticks into each side of face for whiskers.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease bread pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until done. Cool.
Top with powdered sugar.

title: coconut pumpkin bars
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Set aside.
In a medium bowl, stir crushed cereal, milk, pumpkin and vanilla.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in another bowl, beat shortening and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in pumpkin mixture and add flour mixture.
Mix until well combined.
Spread evenly in greased 9x13-inch pan.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes; drain.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add sour cream and soup.
Combine with cooked potatoes in crock-pot on low heat for at least 1 hour.

title: old fashion dumplings
directions: Sift self-rising flour.
Mix flour, lard and milk together real well.
Add more flour until dough is real stiff.
Pinch off small amount and roll out on floured board as thin as possible. Sprinkle black pepper on dough.
Cut in small pieces and drop in boiling broth in which you've cooked your chicken.
Take meat off the bones; drop in with dumplings.

title: lazy man's pie
directions: Melt margarine in 2-liter casserole dish in 350° oven.
Mix flour, baking powder, sugar, salt, milk and cinnamon in a small bowl.
Pour this over the melted margarine.
Drop on top of this the cut-up peaches or fruit of choice along with syrup.
Bake until crust rises through fruit and browns.

title: pizza crust dough
directions: Mix water and yeast.
Add salt and oil.
Mix in flour.
Raise 2 hours.
Makes 2 pizzas.

title: party cherry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries.
Add lemon juice and enough water to syrup to make 3 1/2 cups of liquid.
Heat to boiling.
Dissolve gelatin in hot liquid.
Divide into 2 equal portions.
Chill 1 portion until partially set.
Add pineapple pieces.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Add cream to softened cream cheese.
Spread over jello.
Chill until firm.
Chill remaining until thick.
Add nuts and cherries.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Chill.

title: evalynn marr's brownies
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until thick.
Add cocoa and butter that have been melted together.
Beat until smooth.
Add flour; mix in chopped nuts.
Bake in slow oven (325°) 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut in squares while warm.
Makes 2 dozen squares.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain. Cook noodles and drain (I use a little butter after draining to keep them from sticking together. Can use 1/2 box for 4 to 6 people.) Layer small amount of spaghetti sauce in bottom of dish. Put 1/2 of noodles, 1/2 Ricotta cheese mixture and 1/2 ground chuck. Cover with spaghetti sauce. Cover with lots of Mozzarella cheese. Repeat the layers and top with lots of Mozzarella cheese and cook until bubbly.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Beat until fluffy and pour into greased 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remaining 3 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in frying pan; add onion and green pepper and brown.
Then add tomatoes; simmer for 5 to 10 minutes. Alternate layers of beef and macaroni in baking dish.
Place cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.
If you like, you may add chili powder to the ground beef.

title: grudge fudge candy
directions: Boil sugar and milk together in large kettle for 10 minutes, stirring to keep from sticking.
Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients.
Stir until everything has melted (do not beat). Pour into 10 x 14-inch buttered pan.
Refrigerate for about 2 hours before cutting.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: ground beef logs
directions: Combine meat, salt, pepper and onion.
Pat out to 10 x 15-inch rectangle.
Cut into 6 (5-inch) squares.
Combine crumbs, cheese, carrots, butter and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread mixture over meat sections in equal amounts.
Roll up.
Wrap each with bacon slice.
Fasten with toothpick.
Roast on rack in baking dish about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: artichoke supreme
directions: Mix together and bake in a small buttered casserole for 10 minutes at 350°. Serve as hot appetizer with crackers or with cocktail size rye bread.

title: honey mustard beef ribs
directions: In saucepan, combine butter, green and yellow onions and garlic.
Cook over low heat 15 minutes or until onions are tender. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients except ribs.
Grill ribs on covered grill 30 to 35 minutes, brushing ribs generously with honey mustard until meat is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well in large pan, then add enough broth to moisten the mixture well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling hot.
Serve with baked turkey, chicken, duck, goose, bear, venison, antelope or your choice of meat and giblet gravy.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Blend in flour, vanilla and salt.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch loose bottom tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
Cool on rack.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until set, but not brown.
While warm, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: vegie squares
directions: Sprinkle on top of cream cheese mixture.
Pat down and chill overnight.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: nacho dip
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the beans, softened cream cheese, salsa and Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 40 minutes at 325°.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: pecan log
directions: Melt marshmallows.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Roll into shape.
Roll in crushed pecans; refrigerate.

title: holiday fruit pudding
directions: Beat egg in saucepan.
Stir in sugar, cornstarch and salt. Stir in milk; cook and stir over medium heat until thickened. Cook and stir 1 minute longer.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Add fruit.
Cool before serving.
Serves 6.

title: microwave mochi
directions: In
a
microwavable bowl, mix sugar and mochi-ko first, then add
water and stir until smooth.
Cover with Saran Wrap, cook on High
for 3 minutes and stir smooth.
Cover again and cook additional	2
minutes,
or
until	done, and stir until smooth. (It's
easier using a wooden mallet type stick if one is available,	if
not,
a
wooden spoon will do.)

title: old time spice cake
directions: May add raisins and nuts.
No directions given.
Very good.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Season chicken parts with salt, pepper and paprika.
Saute in shortening until slightly browned.
Add the four cups water, bay leaves and peppercorns.
Cover and cook slowly until tender and chicken falls away from the bones.
You may need to add more water.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix together first three ingredients.
In separate bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients to liquids.
Stir to moisten.
Fold in 3/4 cup blueberries.
Batter should be lumpy.
Fill greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: steak casserole
directions: Brown steak and onions in butter.
Add mushrooms and salt and pepper to taste.
Add sour cream and simmer.
Serve over a bed of rice or noodles.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix jello, hot water and sugar.
Let cool.
Add to other ingredients.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: all-bran yeast rolls
directions: Combine All-Bran, margarine, sugar and salt in bowl.
Pour in 1 cup boiling water.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Combine with All-Bran mixture and add flour, a little at a time, mixing well.
Cover and let rise twice in warm place.
Form dough into rolls and let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: molasses cake
directions: Stir well together, then add 1/2 cup water with 1 teaspoonful soda dissolved in it; bake in layers at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add soup and water.
Place in glass baking dish.
Put cheese on top of meat mixture.
Line Tater Tots on top.
Bake for 30 minutes or until Tots are browned.

title: vegetable curry
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion.
Saute 7 to 8 minutes.
Add garlic and spices.
Saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and water.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Simmer 15 to 25 minutes (until vegetables almost tender).
Add peas. Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: ritzy baked chicken
directions: Crush Ritz crackers until very fine.
Melt butter and dip chicken in it.
Then roll chicken in crackers.
Bake on cookie sheet, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients then add oil, egg, and water. Mix and spoon into greased muffin tin, about 1/2 to 3/4 full. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Remaining mixture can be stored in refrigerator for 1 week in air tight container.

title: yake soba
directions: Put small amount of oil in cooker. Brown meat (do not flour) and onions. Add carrots and cabbage. Saute well.

title: chicken fried burgers
directions: Combine beef, onion, salt, and pepper, mix well.
Shape into six patties.
Dip patties in beaten egg, then in coating mix. Slowly brown on both sides in small amount of hot shortening, about 15 mins.

title: coconut cheese pie
directions: Spread or rub butter into pie pan.
Spread 1 1/3 cups coconut and mash to make a pie shell.
Mix remainder of ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: potato-nut croquettes
directions: Steam potatoes until tender; cool and peel.
Make white sauce by blending together flour and water and cooking over medium heat until thick.
Allow sauce to cool to room temperature.
Mash potatoes and add sauce and blend well.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Shape into patties and bake on pans that have been lightly sprayed with Pam at 350° until brown.
Serve with gravy.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, sift together the flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in the grated carrots, raisins, nuts, coconut and apple.
Beat together eggs, oil and vanilla.
Stir into flour mixture just until moistened. Spoon batter into well-greased muffin tins.
Bake 20 minutes. Paper liners work well and will make 24 muffins.

title: french bread
directions: Cut loaf in half horizontally.
Blend butter and dressing. Spread on bread.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chili with beans and rice
directions: Brown meat and pour off fat.
Add tomato juice, beans, rice and seasoning.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Yields 5 servings.

title: southern potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes in cubes. Cook, drain and mash. Add cut up boiled eggs and all other ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: stone crock cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, spices and salt.
Dissolve coffee in the water and add to mixture. Add nuts and dates.
Can use other things instead.
Drop by teaspoon and bake at 350°.

title: texas hash
directions: Combine meat, onions and pepper; brown in skillet.
Add tomatoes, rice and seasonings.
Pour into covered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: aunt minnie's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add sugar slowly.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, soda and salt, sifted together; alternate with sour cream.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Put in cold oven.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar slowly.
Beat eggs; blend into this. Add milk, baking soda and flour.
Next, add vanilla, nuts and bananas.
Bake in 2 layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Fudge icing goes great with this.

title: naked salad
directions: Tomatoes:
Cut into small bowl with one clove of garlic and seal bowl.

title: glazed carrots
directions: In 1 1/2-quart microproof baking dish, stir cornstarch and water until smooth.
Stir in corn, syrup, margarine and spice. Add carrots; toss to coat well.
Cover.
Microwave at High 6 to 9 minutes.
Stir after 3 minutes; let stand 2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Combine pineapple, orange segments, sugar and cottage cheese. Add dry jello.
Mix well.
Fold in cool whip.
Refrigerate a least 2 hours before serving.

title: spinach meatballs
directions: Drain spinach, squeezing out as much liquid as possible. Combine with beef, egg, bread crumbs, onions and oregano in medium bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place in single layer on jelly roll pan.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes.
Turn and bake another 5 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Remove meatballs and place in shallow 1 quart casserole.
Pour sauce over meatballs, cover and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until meatballs are cooked through and sauce is hot.
Serve over pasta, sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: super pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Beat 3 minutes or until mixed well.
Pour into greased baking pan or tube cake pan. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
(If oven cooks fast, cook at 325° until done.)

title: oyster dressing(turkey side dish)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in ovenproof casserole. Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour or until browned on top and firm.

title: calvary baptist punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar with a little water in a gallon milk jug.
Add pineapple juice and finish filling nearly to top with water.
Freeze until several hours before serving.
Let thaw until slushy.
Add punch and Sprite together in punch bowl. Serve.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: layered casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain off excess drippings.
Stir in taco seasoning, chilies and tomatoes.
Place 1/2 the chips in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer 1/2 meat mixture and 1/2 shredded Monterey Jack cheese.
Repeat and top with sour cream and Cheddar cheese.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Great with pork and chicken.

title: pizza swiss steak
directions: Season	steak
with salt and pepper.
Roll in flour and brown steak in skillet.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over steak; top with onion slices.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cover and bake 1 hour or until tender in a 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: pintos with cornbread topping
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
You can reverse this and use the topping on the bottom and beans on top, either way, it's great. Simmer over medium heat for 10 minutes pintos, onion, tomato sauce and green pepper.

title: fried chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper. Coat with flour. In large skillet, heat 1/2-inch oil (about 2 1/2 cups) over medium-high heat to about 400°. Add chicken, skin side down. Place larger pieces in center. Fry 10 minutes or until crisp and golden. Cover and cook 5 minutes longer. Turn chicken. Reduce heat to medium. Cover and cook 10 minutes. Uncover and cook 5 minutes, crisp skin. Remove chicken and drain on paper towel.

title: cottage cheese jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add ingredients in order.
Pour into mold.

title: oreo cake
directions: Break cookies into small pieces.
Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt butter and pour over cookies.
Mix pudding, milk and cream cheese.
Pour over cookies.
Slice bananas over top of pudding.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in halves; take out yolks.
Place egg whites on tray. Combine egg yolks with remaining ingredients; mix well.
Place filling back into egg whites.
Garnish with paprika.

title: lime chicken
directions: Very lightly brown chicken tenders in oil.
Remove chicken and blot oil out of skillet.
Squeeze lime into skillet.
Simmer lime juice until bubbly and almost evaporated.
Add butter and stir until melted.
Add herbs, salt and pepper.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Add cooked chicken, stirring until chicken is coated with lime sauce. Serve immediately.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: casserole dinner
directions: Starting with potatoes, put vegetables in layers in a 2-quart casserole, reserving about 1/3 of the pepper, celery and onion. Sprinkle each layer with part of the salt and pepper.
Mix tomato soup and water.
Pour over meat and potato layers.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours. Serves 6.

title: the "best" brownies(hershey's)
directions: Blend oil, sugar and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in a 9-inch square greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. There's something different about these brownies.

title: stuff cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up cabbage like you were going to fry it. Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish with lid. Brown meat and onion. Drain any fat drippings. Add salt and pepper to taste. Add Special Sauce and water. Season to taste with some garlic powder and red pepper. Add rice. Mix well. Pour over cabbage. DO NOT STIR! Meat will be on top. Put lid on dish. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Take from oven, stir and bake for another 45 minutes with lid on dish.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Mix cake mix per directions.
Add apples and nuts.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Mix milk, sour cream and lemon juice and put over cake.
Bake 10 more minutes. Sprinkle cinnamon if desired.

title: chicken finale
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: low-fat fruit salad
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Put in refrigerator to cool.
Ready to eat.
Tastes great with graham crackers.

title: ohio brownies
directions: Cream sugar, cocoa and margarine. Add eggs and flour and beat well. Stir in the nuts. Mixture will be thick. Place mixture into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased cake pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. While hot, cover the cake with 1 package of miniature marshmallows. Cover the pan with a dish towel to retain the heat.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until well blended.
Add the next 5 ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour in a 325° oven.

title: hamburger and potato casserole
directions: Line bottom of buttered Pyrex pie dish with hamburger patties. Slice potatoes and layer on top of patties.
Pour soup (slightly diluted with water) over hamburger patties and potatoes.
Bake at 425° until done.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix in skillet and cook until syrup begins to brown and peanuts start popping. Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon soda and beat for 1 minute. Spread on a greased baking sheet.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well. Cook over medium heat to soft ball.
Add vanilla and butter.
Beat it until it gets stiff and pour it in greased pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Don't give up beating.
It takes a while.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onions in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes, approximately, or until toothpick comes out clean. Bake in 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: cauliflower and asparagus casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower according to package directions or microwave at High for 12 to 14 minutes.
Place cauliflower in greased 2-quart casserole.
Arrange asparagus over the cauliflower.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil sugar, water, cornstarch and strawberry Jell-O together until thick.
Set aside to cool.
Cook pie shell and cool.
Put whole or sliced strawberries into cooled pie shell and pour cooled filling on top of berries.
Top with Cool Whip.
Makes 1 pie.

title: frankfurter crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll each hot dog in dough.
Brush with egg.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: pecan roll
directions: Mix all this together and roll into a log. Roll this
in the pecans.

title: garden club punch
directions: Place frozen strawberries in punch bowl.
Pour pineapple juice, Hawaiian Punch, ginger ale and orange juice over strawberries.
Let stand for 30 minutes or more before serving. Stir gently to mix.
Yields 60 servings.

title: fruit delight
directions: Chop apple and banana. Mix in yogurt. Chill and serve.

title: coffee crunch cake
directions: Mix together.
Flour and grease pan.
Cook at 400° for 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: baked eggplant(low calorie, low sodium)
directions: Cook eggplant in clear water until tender.
Saute onion in margarine.
Dampen whole wheat bread crumbs.
Drain water from eggplant and mix everything together.
Put in nonstick baking dish and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: gazebo soup
directions: Saute the onions, celery and carrots in the margarine for 15 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Heat until all is mixed well and then serve.

title: mexican chip dip
directions: Mix all together in crock-pot.
Serve with chips.

title: chocolate coconut pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and water in a cup until smooth.
Place remaining ingredients (except pie shells) in a saucepan.
Add cornstarch and mix well.
Cook and stir over low heat until thick. Pour into pie crust.

title: liver pate ball
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well, kneading with your fingers. Form into ball.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill 2 hours.
I put some Cool Whip and nuts on top, also.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Pour coconut and pecans in the bottom of the pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour this over the coconut and pecans.
Mix the cream cheese, melted butter and sugar.
Spoon this over the cake batter.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: scallops piccata
directions: Squeeze the juice from one lemon, set aside.
Thinly slice the other lemon for garnish.

title: custard ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until yolks and whites are blended. Add sugar and salt. Scald milk. Add sugar-egg mixture to milk, stirring constantly. Cook over hot water until mixture coats a spoon. Remove from heat. Cool by placing pot in cool water or by refrigeration. Pour into gallon freezer.
Add vanilla, almond and evaporated milk. (Allow about 3 inches of custard from top of freezer.) Freeze in freezer.

title: easy swiss cheese bread
directions: Take bread and cut it into 1-inch slices, being sure not to cut all the way through the loaf.
Place loaf on foil with enough foil to cover loaf.
Place 1 slice of folded Swiss cheese into each cut.
Butter top and sides of loaf with mixture of remaining ingredients.
Wrap bread in the foil and bake about 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: light and airy bread buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, add sugar and salt.
Melt butter and shortening mix and add to yeast mixture.
Add beaten eggs and 4 cups flour to make thick batter.
Allow to sit covered for 1/2 hour.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon and put aside. Saute chopped onion and chopped celery in drippings. Add potatoes and chicken soup plus 1 cup water.
Cook until potatoes are done, then add corn.
Heat milk and margarine separately, then add it to chowder mixture. Delicious.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Add cheese, soup, Pet milk, rice and broccoli.
Mix all together.
Bake in casserole dish at 300° for 1 hour.

title: miracle brownies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and corn syrup. Sift first 5 ingredients.
Add to mix.
Beat 2 minutes at low speed.
Stir in nuts, reserving some for top of batter.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: laura bell's vegetable casserole
directions: Cook limas and green beans, according to directions.
Add peas.
Drain well.
Mix.
Chop onion or grate.
Add onion and water chestnuts to vegetables.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Mix well.
Add mayonnaise and mix. Put in casserole dish and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly or brown.

title: mexican stuffed shells
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Combine picante sauce, water and tomato sauce.
Stir 1/2 cup of sauce mixture into meat.
Add chilli peppers, 1/2 cheese and 1/2 French fried onions.
Mix well.
Pour 1/2 of remaining sauce in bottom of casserole dish.
Stuff shells with meat mixture and put in casserole dish.
Pour remaining sauce over shells.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop all of the stems away from broccoli, leaving just the flowers.
Wash and drain well.
Mix vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise or dressing well with wire whip; add raisins, bacon, broccoli and cheese.
Stir all together until well coated.
Delicious and keeps about 4 days.

title: green bean dish
directions: Cut beans into small sections.
Peel skin from potatoes and dice up.
Cut bacon into small pieces and dice up onion.
Add all of the ingredients together in a pan.
Add salt, pepper and water. Let boil until tender.
Enjoy!

title: stroganoff supreme
directions: Brown meat in oleo.
Add onions, mushrooms and seasoning. Cook until tender.
Add cream cheese and milk.
Continue cooking until cheese melts.
Serve over noodles.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes, onions and celery slowly until tender; set aside.
Melt butter.
Remove from heat and add flour.
Heat milk (do not boil).
Add butter mixture to milk.
Now add potatoes. Cook another 5 minutes.
Serve hot with cornbread or hoecakes. Very good!!

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat 4 ounces of cream cheese and onions until blended.
Save for topping.
Beat 4 ounces cream cheese, 1 1/4 cups of each cheese, chilies and cumin until blended.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well.
Warm tortillas in lightly oiled skillet.
Place 2 tablespoons of Cheddar mixture on each tortilla.
Roll up.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Top with enchilada sauce and remaining cheeses.
Bake 20 minutes.
Top with cream cheese mixture and olives.

title: breakfast nog
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Sugar may be added if desired.
Yields a little over a quart.

title: nestles crunchy fudge sandwiches
directions: Heat chips with peanut butter until mixture is smooth.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well; press half of mixture in 8 x 8-inch pan and refrigerate.
Combine remaining ingredients over hot (not boiling) water and stir until smooth.
Spread over first mixture. Top with remaining peanut butter mixture, press gently. Refrigerate until firm (1 hour).
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: chicken capoline
directions: Cook chicken in broth, remove and dice, set-aside.
Next cook vegetables in broth, remove.
Mix together wine vinegar, soy sauce and brown sugar.
Add to chicken broth and simmer 1 minute.
Add chicken and vegetables back to the broth.
Cook pasta in boiling water, drain and add to the chicken mixture.

title: bread pudding
directions: Meringue:
Beat 10 egg whites in a bowl.
Beat well; when stiffening begins, put 1/2 teaspoon baking powder in and beat until stiff.
Add 3/4 cup sugar and beat until sugar melts.

title: taboule
directions: Chop parsley, tomatoes and onions.
Mix all ingredients with lemon juice, oil, salt, pepper, mint and add the burgul last.

title: snack mix
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: easy fruit jelly
directions: In heavy pan, bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon alum.
Boil 2 minutes.
Jar and seal.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger.
Layer in pan:
noodles, sauce, cheese, noodles, sauce, cheese until full.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix cake mix, oil and 1 egg until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup. Pat remainder into a 13 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Mix cream cheese, sugar, 1 egg and lemon juice until light and fluffy (3 to 4 minutes). Pour over baked layer. Crumble the reserved mixture over the top. Bake another 15 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat; cut up into cubes. Cut up potatoes, onions and carrots. Mix with meat in soup pot; add water to cover. Cook approximately 25 minutes, then add vegetables and beef stew seasoning.

title: barbecue-baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for approximately 50 to 60 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Mustard, brown sugar and barbecue sauce can be adjusted to meet your own taste. If you want slightly hotter, can add couple of dashes hot sauce.

title: colcannon(a great irish dish. goes fabulous with corned beef and cabbage.)
directions: Boil potatoes in water until tender; drain and set aside. In medium frying pan, cook bacon until brown. Add diced Spanish onion and saut with bacon until translucent. Add cabbage and vinegar and cook until cabbage is tender.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: About 1 1/4 hours before serving, spread chicken breasts flat. Fold cheese and ham slices to fit on top.
Fold breasts over filling and fasten edges with toothpicks.
On waxed paper, mix flour and paprika.
Use to coat chicken.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat and pour into large uncooked shell. Bake at 350° until done in center, 30 minutes or more.

title: herbed olive oil
directions: Will need 10 ounce bottle (decorative bottles are great).

title: lazy-day coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and sour cream; mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and nutmeg.
Add to batter and mix well.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: easy crust chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken in water.
Debone and place chicken pieces in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Heat broth and soup and pour over chicken, adding salt and pepper to mixture.
Mix flour, milk and melted margarine.
Pour over chicken and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: carrot salad
directions: Grate the carrots. Dice 1 apple with peel.
Mix other ingredients in with carrots and apple.
Use the dressing you prefer.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small bite-sized pieces.
Cook in large pan on large stove.
(Takes about 3 weeks.)
This will serve 3,800.
If more are expected, two additional rabbits may be added.
But only do this if necessary, as most people do not like to find hare in their stew.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces. Add chicken to soup, cheese and rice.
Mix all together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve while hot.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix ingredients, adding the peaches and syrup last.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Lay bread on bottom of dish.
Place cooked meat over bread layer.
Pour egg and milk mixture over meat. Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake next day at 350° for 45 minutes; add cheese for last 15 minutes.

title: banana cupcakes
directions: Mix all together as cake.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Add nutmeats, if desired.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Stir ingredients with spoon. Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Use 2 or 3 loaf pans.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Stir flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt into mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until dry ingredients are moistened. Pour into greased Bundt pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or a little longer in Bundt pan.
Serve with soft cream or whipped cream dabbed with applesauce.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Put vegetables, melted cheese and 1/2 stick of margarine in casserole dish.
Top with Ritz crackers and 1 stick melted margarine.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: shake and bake chicken
directions: One pan cornbread.
Several pieces of stale bread, broken in pieces.
If you have any leftover biscuits, use them.
Set this aside in large pan.

title: country chicken and potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut unpeeled potatoes into chunks. Chop onion.
In large roasting pan, toss potatoes and onion with chicken, salt, rosemary and pepper.
Arrange the chicken pieces skin side up; bake, uncovered, 1 hour or until potatoes are tender and browned.
Add a few pats of margarine on top of chicken before baking if you like.
Baste the chicken and potatoes occasionally. Serves 8.

title: cheddar-onion bundt
directions: Thaw dough according to directions.
Slice each loaf into 12 equal pieces.
Punch hole in each piece and fill with cheese. Form into ball to enclose cheese.
Combine melted butter and dry onion soup mix.
Dip each ball of dough in butter and onion mixture.
Place dipped piece of dough in 12-cup Bundt pan or tube pan.
Cover.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove immediately from pan and serve warm.

title: baked turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 475°. Prepare turkey for cooking. Wash turkey and clean out turkey cavity. Put turkey in roasting pan. Stuff turkey with onion, celery and apple.
Melt oleo and pour over turkey.
Salt and pepper real good all over turkey. Add warm water.
Put in a tightly closed roaster and bake at 475° for 1 hour.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine, mix and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 425° (or less).
Serves 6 to 8.

title: moist 'n creamy coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package in 9x13 inch pan.
Cool 15 minutes; then poke holes in cake with fork.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease a bundt or tube pan. Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces. Mix cinnamon and sugar together. Roll biscuits in cinnamon mixture and place in bundt pan.

title: old fashioned potato soup
directions: Heat water with salt to boiling in 2-quart pan.
Cube potatoes and cook in salted water.
Cook bacon, saving grease.
Cook potatoes until tender, then drain, saving the water.
Then brown the potatoes in the bacon grease.
While the potatoes are browning, mix the flour and beaten egg.
Add these to the potato water, stirring to separate and make riviets.
Cook until thick.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon and hamburg; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients in a large saucepan or crock-pot.
Simmer.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream butter well.
Add flour slowly.
Blend and add cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Shape into long rolls, wrap in waxed paper.
Keeps in freezer indefinitely.
Keeps in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Melt gelatine in 1/2 cup hot water. Heat tomato soup and blend in softened cream cheese. Add gelatine and rest of ingredients. Blend well. Pour into ring mold and refrigerate until set. Serve with various crackers.

title: no-crust lite banana cream pie
directions: Spread bananas on bottom of a 9-inch pie pan.
In blender, mix yogurt and cottage cheese.
Mix gelatin and water and heat on low until dissolved.
To yogurt mixture, add sugar and vanilla; blend. Slowly add gelatin, blending.
Pour over bananas and chill until firm (2 to 4 hours).
This is also good in a graham cracker crust, but then it's no longer fat free.

title: tostadas
directions: Cook beef on medium and cook until done.
Put chili in and cook for 15 minutes together.
Put beans in blender.
After they are blended real soft, put in with the beef and chili mixture. Mix together real good.
Put in chili powder and simmer for 2 or 3 hours or use crock-pot.
Put the mixture on toastada shells.
Put grated cheese, chopped tomatoes and lettuce on top.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: In skillet, melt margarine, saute chicken cut into 2-inch pieces, onion, pepper and garlic for 5 minutes.
Add rice and cook 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes and their liquid, broth, parsley, basil and Tabasco sauce.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes, covered.
Add shrimp and peas, cover and simmer for 3 minutes.

title: sunday dinner hot rolls
directions: Mix first three ingredients and let stand for 30 minutes.
Mix flour, salt, eggs and melted butter.
Add to first mixture.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: fried cauliflower with mustard dip(the frying is a pain, but the flavor rocks!)
directions: Wash cauliflower and break into florets.
Combine eggs, milk, flour, salt and pepper.
Stir until smooth.
Dip florets in batter and dredge in cracker meal.
Deep fry at 375 degrees and drain on paper towels. Mustard Dip: 1 cup mayonnaise, 2 Tbsp. grated onions, 1 Tbsp. Dijon mustard, 1 Tbsp white wine vinegar, 1/2 tsp. curry powder.
Combine all and mix well.
Chill 2-3 hours before serving.
Goes well with raw vegetables as well.

title: a-b-c casserole
directions: Cook asparagus, broccoli and cauliflower according to package directions.
Drain.
Combine with water chestnuts, cheese, margarine and soup in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into greased 6 x 9-inch dish.
Dot with melted margarine; sprinkle with crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: hugs and kisses brownies
directions: Make package of brownies as directed in a 9x13 pan. Carefully top warm brownies with candies. One for each brownie. Approx. 20 squares.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook beef, onion, salt and pepper, stirring with fork until meat loses its red color.
Blend in flour; add 1 1/4 cups water, then the Worcestershire sauce and ketchup.
Simmer, stirring occasionally for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot on buns.
Serves 8.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and quarter apples. Roll each quarter in a roll. Place in baking dish (8 rolls). Melt margarine, sugar, cinnamon and water. Pour over rolls with apples. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in oleo until soft.
Mix with all other ingredients and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 300° for about 30 minutes.

title: squash patties
directions: Grate squash, onion and cheese.
Mix all ingredients well; pat out into patties.
Fry until golden brown on each side.

title: chewy peanut butter coconut bars
directions: Cream peanut butter, shortening and sugars together until fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat well.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Add coconut; mix until just blended.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for about 25 minutes until golden.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Grind cranberries, apples, whole oranges and pecans together.
Add pineapple with juice and sugar.
Stir together; allow sugar to dissolve.
Add to jello.
Place in bowl and refrigerate.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: Saute the onion in butter until tender.
Add the juice from the clams, the seasonings, the condensed cream of mushroom soup and the white wine.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, bring 4 quarts of water to a boil.
Cook 1/2 pound linguine according to package directions.
Add the clams to the sauce and heat thoroughly, but do not boil (clams toughen when cooked too much).
Drain cooked linguine and serve with clam sauce.
Serves 6; approximately 280 calories per serving.

title: hoodish
directions: Cut meat up into chunks.
Boil in a little water with onion until beef is done and tender.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with buttered rice.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in melted butter.
When soft, add cream of mushroom soup.
Add soup first, then fill can with 1/2 cup water. Stir and mix well, then pour into onion, margarine and mushroom soup.
Drain beans.
Make 2 layers.
Put 1 can green beans in casserole dish.
Add 1/2 of sauce of onion, margarine and mushroom soup.
Add 1/2 cracker crumbs.
Add 1/2 grated cheese.
Repeat for second layer.
Top with can of dried French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in fruit and pecans. Pour 1/2 of gelatin mixture into oiled 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish. Chill until firm.
Store remaining mixture at room temperature. Spread sour cream over congealed fruit mixture.
Spoon remaining gelatin mixture over sour cream.
Cover and chill until firm. Yields 12 servings.

title: party chicken
directions: Skin and bone chicken breasts.
Wrap each with 1/2 slice of bacon.
Cover bottom of flat greased baking dish with chipped beef.
Place chicken breasts on chipped beef.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over all.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours uncovered.

title: new england cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, then eggs.
Add flour and spices. Dissolve soda in small amount of hot water and add to sugar mixture.
Stir in raisins.
Spread in sheet pan, very thin.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 20 minutes.
While warm, frost sparingly with powdered sugar and milk glaze and cut into squares.

title: peach fuzz buzz
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend well.
Serve in champagne glasses.
Yields 5 to 6 drinks.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer on large plate starting with beans and ending with cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: cornflake-peanut butter candy
directions: Bring first
3	ingredients to a good boil. Remove from heat. Add
the
peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme. Stir this together well.
Add enough cornflakes to work together.
Pour into a
13 x 9-inch lightly buttered pan. Smooth quickly as it hardens. Cut into squares.

title: master mix(baking mix)
directions: Sift baking powder, salt, sugar and cream of tartar into flour.
Sift all together twice into a large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Store in tightly covered container at room temperature.
Will keep for 6 weeks. When ready to use in a recipe, pile Master Mix lightly into measuring cup and level with spatula to measure.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Mix well together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with 1 cup crushed corn flakes mixed with 2 tablespoons melted butter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: lemon cream scones
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in raisins and lemon peel.
With a fork, stir in cream and enough water needed to make it come together in a rough mass.
On a lightly floured surface, knead dough 5 times. Place on a greased cookie sheet and pat into an 8-inch circle. With a sharp knife, cut halfway through dough to mark into 12 pie-shaped wedges.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes, until golden brown. Remove to a wire rack to cool.
Cut into wedges while still warm. Serve warm or at room temperature.
Makes 12 scones.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and set aside.
Mix moist ingredients together.
Wash zucchini, slice lengthwise.
Scoop out seeds; leave skin on to shred.
Gradually add dry ingredients to first batter.
Bake at 325° approximately 1 hour.
Makes 2 large or 3 small loaves.

title: golabki(stuffed cabbage leaves)
directions: Cut out core from cabbage.
Pull off and save 12 outer leaves; chop remaining cabbage and set aside.
Immerse leaves in boiling water about 3 minutes or until limp; drain.
Cut out center vein of cabbage leaves, keeping each leaf in one piece.
Cook chopped cabbage, uncovered, in boiling water 2 to 3 minutes; drain and set aside.
Cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Add kelp, if desired; salt and pepper.
Stir in rice and dill.
Remove from heat.
Place about 1/4 cup of meat mixture on each cabbage leaf; fold in sides. Starting at unfolded end, roll up each leaf, making sure folded sides are included in roll.
Place half of the chopped cabbage in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange cabbage rolls, seam side down, atop.
Cover with remaining cabbage.
Pour broth over all.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: pea and bean salad
directions: Drain beans, pimentos and peas; chill.
Add other ingredients and toss lightly.
Should stand overnight before serving.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and milk in mixing bowl. Set aside until you have melted margarine.
Use 10 x 12-inch pan and melt margarine.
Let cool; then add batter, then fruit.
Mix into batter.
Bake at 350° until top is golden brown, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple pineapple cake
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan in the order listed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
After 30 minutes, you may cover pan with foil to prevent coconut from burning.

title: black cherry and peach crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking dish. Combine peaches and lemon juice in baking dish; top with cherries. Thoroughly mix remaining ingredients together and sprinkle over cherries.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until topping is golden brown.

title: bavarian cream
directions: Add Jell-O to 2 cups boiling water, dissolve well, then add 2 cups cold water.
Put into refrigerator.
When Jell-O thickens, add Cool Whip and whip. Stir in fruit and refrigerate for 1 hour or until set.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Soak bread in water 2 to 3 minutes.
Add eggs and mix well. Combine with ground beef, cheese, parsley, salt, oregano and pepper.
With wet hands, form into small balls.
(Makes about 24.)
Brown slowly in hot oil.
Serve as appetizers or with spaghetti.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa in top of double boiler; add milk and egg. Cook mixture until thick. Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla. Stir until mixed well. Pour into baked pie shell. Cover with Cool Whip or meringue. Chill.

title: caramel apples
directions: Wash each apple.
Put a little water in a crock-pot; turn it on high.
Put the caramels in the pot to melt.
Put popsicle sticks in the top of the apples.
Twist the apple into the melted caramels and coat with a wooden spoon.

title: "jurassic park" stew
directions: Cut
up
dinosaur,
using
sharp stone axes, into bite-sized pieces.
(Allow
6	months	time
to do this.) Cook over smoldering	volcano
at 625° until well done (approximately 60 days and 60 nights), stirring once.
In another nearby volcanic cauldron
have brown gravy already simmering during last 5 cooking days of stew.
This recipe serves 6,000 people.

title: almond tea
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over tea bags for 5 minutes only. Mix all ingredients plus 2 cups cold water.
Add 2 quarts cold water and heat.

title: cheese and beef dip
directions: Combine cheese, tomato sauce, beef and garlic.
Heat over water in double boiler until cheese is melted.
Remove garlic. Remove mixture from heat and add beaten egg.
Age for several days in refrigerator.
Reheat and serve as hot dip with crackers. (Chafing dish works well.)
Makes 3 cups.

title: fried squash or okra
directions: Wash, cut (cut squash thin), salt, and roll in flour.
Fry in skillet of grease or a Fry Daddy.
Pour a raw scrambled egg over cut vegetables before rolling in flour.
This will make a crispy batter.
If frying squash in the skillet it is better to fry 8 to 10 slices at a time like individual patties in the bottom of the skillet.

title: chicken-tomato pilaf
directions: In large frypan, cook mushrooms, onions and garlic in oil until tender.
Stir in reserved mushroom liquid, salt, pepper, thyme and tomatoes, cutting tomatoes into pieces.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in All-Bran, chicken and rice.
Cover tightly and simmer about 35 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: club sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes, dice onions; cook with salt and vinegar for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir often.
Slice peppers in thin strips, add to tomatoes and cook 3/4 hour.
Add sugar, cook on low heat for 15 minutes.
Put in pint jars and process 15 minutes.

title: anything dip
directions: Mix together ingredients in bowl.
Refrigerate a couple of hours.
Serve cold with vegetables, crackers or chips.

title: lettuce-cauliflower salad
directions: Arrange in layers in a large bowl, except mayonnaise/sugar mixture.
Pour mayonnaise/sugar mixture over and mix well.
Stays fresh in refrigerator for several days.
Serves 6 to 8. Delicious!

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix and beat ingredients.
Bake in 2 medium loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes. Remove from pans and cool.

title: lemon broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in 2 tablespoons butter, garlic and water for 15 minutes.
Melt
tablespoons
butter with lemon juice and grated rind.
Pour over broccoli and serve.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine corn, onions, celery, green pepper and pimentos; mix well and set aside.

title: barbecue
directions: Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serve on buns.

title: blender ketchup
directions: Quarter tomatoes; remove stem ends.
Cut peppers into strips and quarter onions. Put in blender, filling until 3/4 full.
Blend at high speed for 4 seconds. Pour into large kettle and add vinegar, sugar, salt, dry mustard, red pepper and spices tied in thin cloth.
Simmer in slow oven at 325° until volume is reduced to 1/2.
Remove spices.
Pour in hot jars.
Process 10 minutes. Makes 5 pints.

title: white house barbecue
directions: Boil pork for 30 minutes per pound in enough water to cover. (Add more, if needed.)
Remove from juices.
Strain meat juice to get 1 cup and let meat cool.

title: pineapple hat dish
directions: Mix all together and pour into ovenproof bowl.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Top with cinnamon and serve.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first two ingredients together in the top of a double boiler on stove with water in bottom only.
Keep stirring occasionally until melted together.
Keep heated about medium heat to stay melted.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Put grated cheese on top and bake 5 more minutes.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Slice, combine and set aside first 3 ingredients.
Combine all ingredients in given order and stir until well blended.
Pour in half of batter.
Arrange 1/2 apple slices and repeat.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Melt margarine and cheese together in microwave.
Mix rest of ingredients with margarine and cheese.
Pour in middle of cookie sheet and pat with hands until cookie sheet is covered.
Make about 1-inch thick.
Let set and cut into squares.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in water.
Change water and boil with bay leaf, celery, onion and ham bone.
Simmer 1 hour.
Dice in the potato.
Fry bacon and set aside.
Add the tomato sauce to the bacon fat and cook together for 10 minutes.
Add to beans. Continue simmering 45 minutes to 1 hour until beans are tender. Garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: rice custard
directions: Soak raisins in brandy; set aside.
In a bowl, put eggs, milk, raisins, sugar, rice and vanilla.
Mix well.
Put in a buttered loaf pan.
Put into a larger pan with water.
Bake 1 hour at 300°. Before putting in oven, sprinkle the nutmeg on top.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat in a Dutch oven; drain off grease.
Add salt and pepper and put in 1 1/2 jars of sauce. Reserve the remainder.
While the meat sauce is heating, cook the pasta.
Drain well.
Combine with sauce.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes in the oven until cheese bubbles.
Slice and serve. Use the remaining spaghetti sauce (heated) in a bowl on the table with the Parmesan cheese as garnish.
Serves 6.

title: fresh fruit pie(strawberry, peach, berry)
directions: Mix fruit, sugar and lemon juice.
Set until all sugar is dissolved.
Measure out 1/4 cup of mixture and 1/4 cup water.
Add 1 envelope of unflavored gelatin.
Boil.
Pour over fruit and set in refrigerator until lightly jelled.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell and cool completely until completely jelled.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In food processor, put apple, orange and cranberries.
Add pineapple.
Mix up jello; add sugar and when cool, add pecans. Put in bowl and let set up and serve.
Keeps a long time in refrigerator.

title: bronze baked ham
directions: Line a large roasting pan with foil.
With sharp knife, score top of ham.
Combine garlic (mashed), mustard, chili sauce, brown sugar (packed) and rum in small bowl.
Mix well. Spread evenly over top and sides of ham.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: 1. Brown garlic and onion in a little oil. Sprinkle some basil and leave in.
2. Mix everything together and simmer with the following
meats that you have already browned: 1 lb pork (chops
or cubes) and 1/2 to 1 lb. of sweet Italian sausage. 3. Must cook several hours over very low heat until sauce thickens. Stir occasionally so that sauce does not
burn.

title: black bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix and shape into 2 long rolls, using a deep baking dish to catch drippings when baking.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 24 hours.
Remove wrap and bake 1 hour at 325°. Immediately remove from baking dish and cool.
Store in foil. Sausage will keep in freezer indefinitely.

title: dry barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Baste meat with vinegar, then sprinkle dry mixture on.
Cook on grill.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Bake chicken in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Drain any excess fat. Continue baking.
Meanwhile, melt butter or margarine and mix in honey, soy sauce, salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
During the last 15 minutes of baking time, pour honey mixture over chicken.
Be sure not to bake honey mixture too long, as not to burn.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli delight salad
directions: Wash, drain and cut broccoli flowerets and small stems into small pieces.
Then add raisins, onion, bacon and sunflower kernels.

title: old fashion potato soup
directions: Wash and peel potatoes, cut into 1-inch cubes.
In large pot put potatoes, 2 quarts water and bring to boil until potatoes are done.
Keep boiling and add butter.
Mix cornstarch in the 6 ounces whole milk.
Add to 1 quart milk and add this mixture to potatoes. Bring to hard boil, stirring until thick.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: baked vegetable omelet
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Layer pepper, cheese, broccoli, tomatoes and Cheddar cheese in an ungreased square baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Beat milk, flour, salt and eggs until smooth; pour over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 to 45 minutes or until egg mixture is set.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: mexican scrambled eggs
directions: Beat eggs in mixing bowl with milk.
Add tomato and pepper and stir well.
Melt butter over low heat in skillet; saute ham 3 minutes.
Pour in egg mixture; cook, stirring frequently with spatula, until set.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle cheese on top of cooked eggs.

title: party chicken
directions: Line greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with dried beef.
Wrap bacon around each chicken breast.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup and pour over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Sprinkle with toasted almonds before serving.

title: italian stuffed zucchini(serves 4)
directions: Cook onions, green pepper, celery and garlic in oil until translucent.
Add to hamburg with egg, bread crumbs, seasoned salt, Italian seasoning and tomato paste (enough to moisten stuffing).

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Toss chicken with soy sauce.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Mix fruit with celery.
Add chicken; mix again.
Chill.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, salt and dry mustard.
In 8 x 12-inch casserole dish, put diced bread (evenly).
Put sauteed sausage evenly over bread.
Cover with grated cheese.
Pour over the egg mixture.
Put in refrigerator 4 to 6 hours, or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Wrap each piece of chicken in a slice of bacon.
Place wrapped chicken in Pyrex dish.
Pour remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken until tender. Remove chicken from bones, chop and set aside.
Combine stuffing, sage, onions, butter and liquids. Mix well.

title: crispy cheese wafers
directions: Combine
cheese
and
margarine.
Mix in Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Add flour and mix well.	Form dough into two rolls,
1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in wax paper and chill for
several hours.
Cut dough into wafers or straws and bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: stir-fry thai shrimp
directions: Place shrimp, 1/2 of the garlic and fish sauce in bowl.
Mix and marinate 10 to 15 minutes; set aside.
Pour 1 teaspoon oil in wok or frying pan on medium-high heat.
Place remaining garlic in pan.
Stir couple times and add long beans, sprinkle sugar and shoyu sauce.
Stir; lower heat and simmer 7 to 10 minutes.
Remove beans from pan.
Return heat to medium-high, add remaining oil and place marinated shrimp in pan.
Stir and add onion.
Add long beans to partially cooked shrimp, stir and turn off heat.
Serve immediately.

title: sugarless pineapple cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine cookie crumbs and oleo.
Press in 8 or 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 6 to 7 minutes.
Add milk to pudding and beat 2 to 3 minutes.
Add cheese, vanilla and cinnamon and blend until smooth.
Fold in pineapple.
Pour into pan and cool in refrigerator for about an hour.
Top with D-Zerta Cool Whip.

title: german corn fritters
directions: Combine corn and eggs. Add dry ingredients and milk. Beat well. Fry in hot oil.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Flour chops; salt and pepper.
Brown on both sides in skillet; need not cook fully.
While chops are browning, slice potatoes in long casserole dish (enough for your meal).
Salt and pepper; add onion if desired and cheese.
Mix celery soup with milk.
Heat in microwave; pour over potatoes.
Top with browned pork chops.
Bake in oven until potatoes stick soft (normally at 350° for 1 hour, depending on the various ovens).

title: hamburger fluff
directions: Brown hamburger in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add salt and celery salt.
Add celery, onion and green pepper.
Simmer slowly for 15 to 20 minutes.
Place in casserole, cover with cooked rice, then layer of peas and top with tomato soup.
Lay strips of bacon over top.
Cover and put in oven at 350°.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes. Remove cover and bake 5 to 10 minutes or until browned.

title: cheese-broccoli soup
directions: In 5-quart pan, melt butter and saute onion for 3 minutes. Add broth and heat to boiling.
Add noodles and salt and boil uncovered for 3 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and garlic and cook 4 more minutes.
Add milk and cheese; pepper to taste and cook until cheese melts.
Don't boil once milk is added.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O with the boiling water.
Mix all ingredients together, except sour cream.
Place half the mixture into a 3-quart casserole*.
Let chill for an hour or two.
Then put the sour cream on top and add the remaining mixture.

title: lentil salad
directions: Place in long shallow dish for one hour turning frequently.

title: squash pickles
directions: Put sliced squash, onions and green pepper in pan and add salt.
Let stand for 1 hour; drain.
Put all the other ingredients in pot.
Add squash, onions and peppers.
Bring
to boil, then boil until clear.
Pack in sterile jars and seal.
Yields about 6 pints.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in large casserole.
Alternate layers of soup, vegetables and onion rings.
Begin with soup and end with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: farmers' breakfast
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in oil until tender-crisp.
Add ham and potatoes; cook until potatoes are tender.
Combine eggs, water and salt; pour over ham mixture.
Cook over low heat, turning occasionally, until eggs are set.
Makes 4 servings.

title: orange sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water.
Remove skins.
Mash potatoes; add remaining ingredients and whip until fluffy.
Put in a medium baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: party salad
directions: Mix the Cool Whip and condensed milk together and refrigerate 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: linda's sin
directions: In a long cake pan, put 1 1/2 sticks butter.
Melt, then add flour.
Stir with fork.
Pat out flat with hand.
Bake until golden brown, about 15 to 20 minutes, at 350°.
Set out and let cool.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip together and pour over cooled crust.
Mix pudding (of your choice) with 1 3/4 cups milk per package so pudding will be thick.
Add Cool Whip to top, then nuts.
It is so very, very good and good for you.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Beat eggs in another bowl.
Beat in milk, oil and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until batter is smooth.
Bake in two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: stack cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Pour into 5 round cake pans. Bake at 350° until done, about 10 minutes.
Cool. Stack in layers, spreading apple butter between each layer and on top.

title: apricot bars
directions: Finely
chop apricots, lemon zest and sugar, reserve the mixture.
Add the eggs and whip until they are light.
When the cookie
base
is
baked, proceed by adding the chopped apricots and
the
baking
powder/salt
to
eggs
and
add
lemon juice. Carefully and evenly pour apricot/egg mixture on top of the hot cookie base
(do
this
by
pouring
the apricot mixture onto a spatula and
letting
the liquid fall from the spatula onto the cookie base).
Bake for 25 minutes.
If the top is not as brown as you would like it to be, turn the broiler on; you must watch very closely.
When
they
are
done,
let
cool,
cut, using a downward
motion
only.
To keep, cover with parchment paper or brown paper.
Saran
Wrap
will ruin the tops of the bars.
You may sprinkle finished bars with powdered sugar.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: To heated skillet, add butter, chopped onions, peppers or olives and mushrooms.
Cook slowly until tender.
Add tomatoes and portion of chicken broth.
Add meat from chicken after it has been cooked until meat falls off bones.
Season with salt and pepper. Cook spaghetti in butter and add chicken mixture to spaghetti. Cook until well blended.
Just before serving, add grated cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat in oven until cheese melts.

title: date nut rolls(mom's)
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Remove and stir in sugar, eggs, and dates.
Cook over low heat stirring until mixture leaves side of pan (about 20 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add all else but coconut; cool.
Shape in rolls and roll in coconut; refrigerate.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine butter and chocolate in a small saucepan; cook over low heat until melted.
Set aside.

title: crispy chicken nuggets
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray a large cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
In paper or plastic bag, combine first 5 ingredients. Shake to mix.
Dip chicken in egg white.
Shake dipped chicken in cereal mixture to coat.
Place on prepared pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes until chicken is no longer pink and coating is crisp.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce or barbecue sauce. Serves 4.

title: acapulco's guacamole
directions: Peel and seed avocados. Grind onions and pepper in mortar (molcajete). Mash avocados and combine with onion mixture. Squeeze juice of 1/2 lemon over avocados and blend well. Add diced tomato and salt; mix well. Serve with crispy tostado chips or hot corn tortillas.

title: meat balls
directions: Form into balls and brown in a skillet.

title: crescent cookies
directions: Mix sugar, flour and vanilla.
Fold in butter.
Add pecans. Shape and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: snicker salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: spring fruit salad
directions: Blend sugar, vinegar, mustard, salt and onion together.
Add oil slowly.
Add poppy seed last.
Arrange lettuce on plates.
Add fruit and avocado. Top with fresh strawberries.
Drizzle dressing over.

title: tomato and scallop chowder
directions: In large pan, heat oil; add onion and celery until soft but not brown.
Add tomatoes, salt, bay leaf and basil.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add water, fish stock and scallops. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Season to taste with pepper.
Remove bay leaf.
Makes 4 servings.

title: holiday punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake as shown on box.
Cool, then crumble up.
In a punch bowl, layer the cake, pouring sweetened milk over cake.
Add the fruit, Cool Whip and pecans in layers, ending with Cool Whip, sprinkled with pecans.

title: mary clark crab cakes
directions: Mix together everything but crabmeat; add it last.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oats and sour cream.
Stir in butter, eggs and brown sugar until well mixed.
Stir together flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Stir into oatmeal mixture just until blended.

title: easy street crab meat dip
directions: Lightly oil a 4-cup (1 quart) mold and set aside.
In a saucepan over medium to low heat, combine the cream cheese and soup and stir until blended.
Sprinkle the gelatin over the mixture and stir until blended.
Stir in the mayonnaise until well combined.
Do not let the mixture boil.
Remove the pan from the heat and carefully blend in the crab meat, onions and celery. Pour the crab mixture into the prepared mold and chill for at least 6 hours.
This recipe can be made up to 2 days in advance.

title: chicken wings pacifica
directions: Arrange wings in a shallow pan.
Heat butter, soy sauce, brown sugar, water and mustard until butter and sugar are melted.
Cool. Pour over wings and marinate at least 2 hours turning twice. Bake at 375° until wings are tender, 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: marinated chops
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Marinate chops 6 to 8 hours or overnight.
Cover, bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Uncover last 15 minutes.

title: pineapple slush
directions: Mix sugar and water and bring to a boil.
Simmer on low heat for 10 minutes.
Combine sugar, water, pineapple juice and rum extract and freeze.
Spoon mixture into glasses and pour lemon-lime soda over ice.
Stir and serve when it becomes slushy.

title: seafood pizza with smoked mozzarella(serves 4)
directions: Cut dough into 4 pieces.
Roll each into 6-inch round and place on baking sheets.
Brush with 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: strawberry short cut cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Combine strawberries and Jell-O.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Blend until moist.
Beat 3 minutes.
Pour batter over marshmallows. Spoon strawberry mixture over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Heat all together.
Marinade for pork chops, chicken, steak or whatever.

title: bisquick yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in sugar, shortening and Bisquick; beat vigorously.
Turn dough onto surface well dusted with Bisquick.
Knead until smooth, about 20 minutes.
Shape as desired.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Cover with damp cloth.
Let rise in warm place (85°), until double, about 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes, depending on size.
Brush with melted butter.

title: pinto bean cakes
directions: Add flour to beans and onion mixture until doughy.
Fry in skillet with cooking oil until golden brown.
Just use about 2 tablespoons mixture at a time for each cake.

title: popovers
directions: Beat the eggs until frothy in a mixer or blender.
Beat in the milk and butter.
Slowly beat in the flour and salt.
The mixture should be light but not foamy.
(If it is bumpy, strain it.)

title: easy chocolate shakes
directions: In a blender, combine milk, pudding mix and mint.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Add ice cubes.
Cover and blend until combined.
Let stand 3 minutes to thicken.
Makes 5 (8 ounce) servings.
Calories:
Fat:

title: lime fluff(congealed salad)
directions: Drain juice from pineapple into saucepan.
Add Jell-O.
Bring to a boil to dissolve Jell-O.
Remove from heat and add pineapple and cottage cheese; stir.
Blend in Cool Whip and nuts, if desired.
Turn into 9 x 9-inch dish and chill.
Cut into squares. Serve on lettuce leaf with crackers.

title: preschool punch
directions: You pour a little coffee in your cup.
Put in some sugar. Stir.
Pour milk.
Stir.
Put the lid on it and you drink it. That's all.

title: fake apple pie
directions: Bring sugar and water to boil.
Dilute cream of tartar with 2 tablespoons of sugar water.
Pour this in the boiling sugar water. Add 23 Ritz crackers and boil 2 minutes (no more, no less).
Do not stir.
Remove from fire and let cool.
Pour mixture in unbaked pie crust.
Add a touch of cinnamon and dot with butter before putting on top crust.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cotton cake
directions: Mix well with mixer.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook in crock-pot for 4 hours.
Garnish with cheese and Doritos.

title: mumu's tomato aspic
directions: Slice up one small bottle olives.
Chop real small best part of stalk of celery.
Dissolve Knox plain gelatine into 1/2 cup cold water.
Put can of whole tomatoes in a bowl and mash to a pulp (juice and all).
Add salt, sugar, grated onion and vinegar. Stir well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together eggs, sugar, oil, salt and vanilla.
Mix zucchini with pineapple and add with mixture.
In separate bowl, combine flour, soda, powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to mixture. Then add nuts and raisins or dates.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oven baked italian potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Rub skins of potatoes with oil; cut in half lengthwise.
Score cut surface of each potato by carefully cutting 1/8 to 1/4-inch deep slices diagonally at 1/2-inch intervals.
Repeat with perpendicular cuts to form a diamond pattern.

title: baked doves
directions: Place doves breast side down in rectangular pan and add 1/2 teaspoon
butter	in
each
breast
cavity.
Sprinkle Worcestershire sauce over bird and gently wrap 1/2 slice bacon over
each dove.
Sprinkle approximately 2 tablespoons cooking sherry over
birds.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil and bake 2 to 3 hours at 300°;
serve with rice or grits.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray an 11 x 14-inch pan with Pam.
Mix sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat with spoon.
Beat in eggs one at a time, then add flour.
Fold in nuts and berries.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Will make about 30 muffins if preferred.

title: chipped ham barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ham, and simmer for 1 hour. Add ham and simmer until ham is warm.
Serve on rolls.

title: salsa
directions: Chop in blender until desired consistency.
Chill before serving.

title: shrimp cocktail appetizer
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of a bowl.
Pour sauce over cream cheese. Put shrimp over cocktail sauce. Serve with crackers.

title: ranch dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Then refrigerate.
Will keep for several days.
I store mine in empty mayonnaise jars.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Flour berries before adding to mixture, then mix all ingredients by hand.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Cook at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: delicious apple cobbler cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9 1/2-inch glass pan.
Combine pie filling, nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour filling in greased pan and spread evenly.
Combine cake mix, oil, eggs and water.
Mix to directions on box.
Pour batter over fruit mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake is done in middle.
Can be served plain or with milk.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Layer tortillas, chicken mixture and cheese.
Repeat with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Cook meat and onion together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomato and enchilada sauces.
